st with this wonderful tour to Templer\'s Park. Step into a world of peace and serenity as you trek through the beautiful jungle surroundings. Let the soothing forest sounds...<br/><br/><b>Inclusions</b>Hotel pickup and drop-off<br/>Transport by air-conditioned minivan<br/><br/><b>Exclusions</b>Food and drinks<br/>Gratuities (optional)<br/>Tour guide<br/><br/><b>Additional Info</b>Confirmation will be received at time of booking<br/>Infants free of charge, no seat<br/>Not recommended for participants with heart complaints or other serious medical conditions<br/>Minimum 2 people per booking required', null, '1.00', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1', null, '1', '', '', null, '', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '', '', '2017-02-21 11:39:20', '6', null, '', 'default');
INSERT INTO `product` VALUES ('23', '', 'https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/tly-production/partner_offers/images/000/003/074/medium/full-day-cameron-highlands-tour-from-kuala-lumpur-in-kuala-lumpur-203243.jpg?1487621737', '', '3074. SKU_IDS: 6767,10821,10822', 'Full-Day Cameron Highlands and Batu Caves Tour from Kuala Lumpur', 'Cameron Highlands is a hill resort at 1,500 meters above sea level with temperatures from 10 - 25 degrees Celsius. It was discovered by a British surveyor Mr William Cameron in 1885.<br /><br />The area is known for its farmlands, tea plantations, orchards, nurseries, waterfalls, rivers, lakes, wildlife, mossy forest, and its local people. Come and find out more on this fabulous tour that gives you a real insight into this area.', '<p>7am: Eat breakfast at your hotel and then depart for the Cameron Highlands. On the way, enjoy a bonus stop at the Batu Caves - a limestone outcrop. Here you will have the opportunity to climb 272 steps into the temple of Hindu Deity, who is honored during the Hindu festival of Thaipusam every year. Proper attire for women is necessary in order to enter the temple. </p>\r\n<p>Next, visit the Cascading waterfalls. The waterfalls cascade into a narrow stream where locals go for a cool dip. The nearby shops sell souvenirs, tribal handicrafts, strange herbs, aphrodisiacs, and tropical fruits.<br /> <br /> Afterwards, learn how the locals use the rain forest for their daily foods at an Aborigine village. You will get to see and experience some local traditions while here.<br /> <br /> 11:30am: stop for lunch and then continue on with visit a to a Tea plantation. The boh tea plantation was founded by a British businessman Mr. J A Russell in 1929. Today boh owns 3 tea estates with 8,000 acres of an undulating, vast carpet of greenery.  The tea plantation works closely with the WWF (World Wildlife Fund) and the MNS (Malaysian Nature Society) to help in the conservation of our elephants and orangutan population. Factory tours are available daily except Mondays. <br /> <br /> Moving forward you will have the chance to visit a butterfly Farm &amp; Insectarium. This secret paradise hosts 5,000 butterflies that dance on ferns and scented flowers. The landscaped gardens, exotic plants, fresh water turtles, and insects are also just as stunning.<br /> <br /> Lastly, handpick fresh strawberries right from the plant at a Strawberry Farm and then take a stroll to see the various vegetables and fruits that thrive in the Cameron Highlands at the vegetable, fruits and flowers market.</p>\r\n5.00pm: Journey back to Kuala Lumpur and arrive back to your hotel at approximately 8pm.<br/><br/><b>Departure Time</b>7am<br/><br/><b>Departure Point</b>Your hotel lobby in Kuala Lumpur<br/><br/><b>Operations</b>Daily<br/><br/><b>Vourcher</b>You can present either a paper or an electronic voucher for this activity.<br/><br/><b>Excerpt</b>Cameron Highlands is a hill resort at 1,500 meters above sea level with temperatures from 10 - 25 degrees Celsius. It was discovered by a British surveyor Mr William Cameron in 1885.<br/><br/><b>Inclusions</b>Lunch<br/>Entrance fees<br/>Professional guide<br/>Hotel pickup and drop-off<br/><br/><b>Exclusions</b>Alcoholic drinks (available to purchase)<br/><br/><b>Additional Info</b>Confirmation will be received within 48 hours of booking, subject to availability<br/>A moderate amount of walking is involved', null, '1.00', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1', null, '1', '', '', null, '', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '', '', '2017-02-21 11:39:21', '6', null, '', 'default');
INSERT INTO `product` VALUES ('24', '', 'https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/tly-production/partner_offers/images/000/003/075/medium/full-day-kampong-tour-from-kuala-lumpur-in-kuala-lumpur-203274.jpg?1487621791', '', '3075. SKU_IDS: 6768,10823,10824', 'Day Trip Inner Countryside Kampong from Kuala Lumpur', 'Experience Malaysia\'s slower pace of life on a day trip from Kuala Lumpur to the tribal region of Carey Island. You\'ll be introduced to the cultural traditions of the Mah Meri seafarers — a subgroup of the aboriginal Senoi people who depend on fishing and agriculture and excel in woodcarvings with mythological symbols. Lunch and round-trip hotel transport are included along with a taste of homegrown toddy, or coconut wine.', 'Your day trip starts with a morning departure from your Kuala Lumpur hotel. After a 2-hour drive into the countryside you\'ll arrive at the Mah Meri village and be greeted by a local aboriginal guide for a comprehensive tour. Learn about cultural traditions while you visit an ancestral home and watch a woodcarving demonstration.<br /><br />At midday you\'ll visit a coconut plantation and watch agile tree climbers harvest coconuts for wine. You\'re served a taste of this unique drink, referred to locally as toddy, which contains an alcohol content of 4 percent.<br /><br />Next, visit a typical Malay home for an herbal garden tour of traditional plants used to treat high blood pressure, cancer, diabetes, and other ailments. A delicious home-cooked meal will be served. After lunch, drive past scenic villages and houses on stilts with photo stops along the way. Finish with a toddy party, accompanied by local snacks such as wild boar, chicken, and mutton, before returning to your hotel in Kuala Lumpur.<strong><br /></strong><br/><br/><b>Departure Time</b>8am<br/><br/><b>Departure Point</b>Your hotel lobby within Kuala Lumpur<br/><br/><b>Operations</b>Daily<br/><br/><b>Vourcher</b>You can present either a paper or an electronic voucher for this activity.<br/><br/><b>Excerpt</b>Experience Malaysia\'s slower pace of life on a day trip from Kuala Lumpur to the tribal region of Carey Island. You\'ll be introduced to the cultural traditions of the Mah Meri seafarers — a...<br/><br/><b>Inclusions</b>Lunch and snacks<br/>Local guide<br/>Hotel pickup and drop-off<br/><br/><b>Exclusions</b>Alcoholic drinks (available to purchase)<br/><br/><b>Additional Info</b>Confirmation will be received within 48 hours of booking, subject to availability<br/>Infant seats are available on request if advised at time of booking', null, '1.00', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1', null, '1', '', '', null, '', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '', '', '2017-02-21 11:39:22', '6', null, '', 'default');
