or mobile copy of certificate upon redemption.<br/>Prior tour booking is mandatory.', null, null, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', null, null, '1', '', '', null, '', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '', '', '2017-02-21 12:08:17', '6', '2017-02-21 12:16:40', '6', 'default');
INSERT INTO `product` VALUES ('123', '', 'https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/tly-production/offers/images/000/000/425/medium/port_dickson_sunset.jpg?1417070924', '', '425', 'PRIVATE TOUR: Port Dickson Beach Escapade & Animal Petting Experience Tour', 'Conveniently located right outside of Kuala Lumpur, Port Dickson Beach is a quick getaway from the city center. Its hidden beaches, mangrove swamps and the historical Cape Rachado lighthouse built by the Portuguese is a reminder of the past.', '**DAY TOUR**\r\n \r\n**Itinerary:**\r\n\r\n* 9.00am: Depart for Port Dickson\r\n* 10.30am: Visit to Ostrich Show Farm   \r\n* 11.30am: Proceed to beach / Free & Easy \r\n* 4.00pm: Return to Kuala Lumpur \r\n\r\n**Good to Note:**\r\n\r\n* This day tour does not include meals.\r\n* Beach sports is suspended until further notice.\r\n* Complimentary airport drop off available if you have a night flight on the day of tour.\r\n\r\n<br>**2D1N TOUR**\r\n\r\n**Itinerary:**\r\n\r\n**Day 1**\r\n\r\n* 9.00am: Depart for Port Dickson.\r\n* 10.30am: Visit to Ostrich Show Farm.\r\n* 11.30am: Proceed to beach / check into hotel / free and easy.\r\n\r\n**Day 2** \r\n\r\n* Morning: Breakfast at hotel / free and easy.\r\n* 12.00pm: Return to Kuala Lumpur.\r\n* 6.00pm: Arrive at Kuala Lumpur. End of tour.\r\n\r\n**Good to Note:**\r\n\r\n* This overnight tour does not include meals.\r\n* Beach sports is suspended until further notice.\r\n* Complimentary airport drop off available if you have a night flight on the second day of tour.\r\n\r\n<br>**Additional Details:**\r\n\r\n**Taman Negara Day Tours**\r\nTel. No: +6012 382 3385\r\nEmail: wintours@gmail.com<br/><br/><b>Departure Time</b>: <br/><br/><b>Departure Point</b>: <br/><br/><b>Operations</b>: <br/><br/><b>Vourcher</b>: <br/><br/><b>Excerpt</b>: Conveniently located right outside of Kuala Lumpur, Port Dickson Beach is a quick getaway from the city center. Its hidden beaches, mangrove swamps and the historical Cape Rachado lighthouse built...<br/><br/><b>Inclusions:</b><br/><br/><br/><b>Exclusions:</b><br/><br/><br/><b>Additional Info:</b><br/>Once you have purchased this tour on Touristly, call +6012 382 3385 or email <a href=\"mailto:wintours@gmail.com\">wintours@gmail.com</a> with your Touristly certificate (or cert. no.), traveler details &amp; preferred tour date to complete your booking.<br/>Tour booking must be made at least 7 days in prior to travel dates.<br/>Present printed or mobile copy of certificate upon redemption.<br/>Prior tour booking is mandatory.', null, null, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', null, null, '1', '', '', null, '', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '', '', '2017-02-21 12:08:18', '6', '2017-02-21 12:16:41', '6', 'default');
INSERT INTO `product` VALUES ('124', '', 'https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/tly-production/offers/images/000/002/475/medium/jadibatek_%283%29.JPG?1433908269', '', '2475', '60-min Batik Drawing Class at Jadi Batek Gallery', 'Jadi Batek Gallery is the only place in Kuala Lumpur where you can meet experience batik artisans, watch then up close as they work and put their finishing touches to the Malaysian batik. Grab the chance to learn the art of batik making with some of the best in the industry.', 'Jadi Batek Gallery strongly believes in preserving our country\'s unique heritage and identity of producing quality batik and handicrafts. Hence, you can be assured that the batik and handicrafts in our gallery are authentic and original, embodying the heart and soul of Malaysian culture and artistry. They are a must-have to complete your journey to this fascinating country.\r\n\r\nWant to learn how to make batik? Try batik painting at Jadi Batek Gallery. Batik classes are available everyday. It provides you with a marvelous opportunity to experiment with batik and produce your own batik masterpiece. Equipment is provided including a piece of cloth, chanting, wax, color and brush. Our friendly artists will guide you all the way during the lessons.\r\n\r\n Stuck for design ideas? We have many designs that you can copy, from cartoon characters to floral patterns, and twin towers to animals. The classes normally take an hour per lesson to complete. After that, we will dry the batik masterpiece you have produced and frame it in a paper frame with plastic for you to bring back home.\r\n<br/><br/><b>Departure Time</b>: 10.00am OR 2.00pm (depending on session selected)<br/><br/><b>Departure Point</b>: Jadi Batek Gallery, 30, Jalan Inai, 55100 Kuala Lumpur, Wilayah Persekutuan Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia<br/><br/><b>Operations</b>: Daily <br/><br/><b>Vourcher</b>: You can present either a paper or an electronic voucher for this activity.<br/><br/><b>Excerpt</b>: Jadi Batek Gallery is the only place in Kuala Lumpur where you can meet experience batik artisans, watch then up close as they work and put their finishing touches to the Malaysian batik. Grab the...<br/><br/><b>Inclusions:</b><br/>60-minute batik wax drawing class<br/>Batik coloring on 30 x 40cm cotton fabric<br/><br/><b>Exclusions:</b><br/>Transportation<br/><br/><b>Additional Info:</b><br/><b>After your purchase on Touristly is confirmed, please complete your booking by emailing <a href=\"mailto:info@jadibatek.com\">info@jadibatek.com</a> or calling +603 2145 1133 with the following details:</b><ul><li>Lead traveler name and contact number</li><li>Number of tour participants</li><li>Preferred class time and date</li><li>Touristly certificate number as booking reference</li></ul><br/>Class booking is mandatory and must be made at least 1 day in advance to avoid disappointment.<br/>In the rare event it is necessary for the local operator to cancel the activity, you will be offered an alternative or full refund.<br/><b>Cancellation Policy:</b><ul><li>Cancellations made at least 2 days prior to the scheduled class booking will be entitled full refund.</li><li>Cancellations made 1 day or less prior to the scheduled class booking is strictly non-refundable.</li></ul>', null, null, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', null, null, '1', '', '', null, '', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '', '', '2017-02-21 12:08:20', '6', '2017-02-21 12:16:43', '6', 'default');
INSERT INTO `product` VALUES ('125', '', 'https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/tly-production/partner_offers/images/000/006/575/medium/half-day-mercedes-benz-with-driver-at-disposal-from-kuala-lumpur-in-kuala-lumpur-277354.jpg?1487621777', '', '6575', 'Half-Day Private Driver from Kuala Lumpur', 'Kuala Lumpur offers a high-end option for discerning travelers who prefer to travel in comfort and style. This 4-hour car hire provides you with your own Mercedes Benz S-class vehicle with a private chauffeur at the wheel. Make an impression while you see the sights in the capital or get dropped at department stores with a sense of flair. The luxury vehicle is at your own disposal, with pickup and drop-off available from hotels in Kuala Lumpur city center.', 'Your personal driver will pick you up from your hotel in downtown Kuala Lumpur at your preferred departure time. Settle into your Mercedes Benz S-class vehicle, which will be at your disposal for the entire 4 hours.<br /><br />In collaboration with your private chauffeur, you have the flexibility to go where you please within the city limits. This luxury form of transportation saves you time so that you can tailor your own itinerary. Skip waiting times for taxis or looking for the subway, which can especially be a hassle during rush-hour traffic. Instead, you\'ll have that all-important sense of freedom that is at the forefront of every discerning traveler\'s schedule.<br /><br />The options are vast while you travel at your own pace: swiftly go from shopping mall to department store; head to Chinatown; or spend time taking that perfect photo of the Petronas Towers before making a stop at the famed Batu Caves. <br /><br />After your explorations, your chauffeur safely brings you back to your hotel in Kuala Lumpur (the airport and accommodations outside the city center are not included).<br/><br/><b>Departure Time</b>: 6am to 11:30pm<br/><br/><b>Departure Point</b>: <p>Your hotel in Kuala Lumpur city center</p><br/><br/><b>Operations</b>: <p>Daily</p><br/><br/><b>Vourcher</b>: You can present either a paper or an electronic voucher for this activity.<br/><br/><b>Excerpt</b>: Kuala Lumpur offers a high-end option for discerning travelers who prefer to travel in comfort and style. This 4-hour car hire provides you with your own Mercedes Benz S-class vehicle with a...<br/><br/><b>Inclusions:</b><br/>Mercedes Class S or similar<br/>Professional driver<br/>Hotel pickup and drop-off<br/>Parking fees<br/><br/><b>Exclusions:</b><br/>Midnight surcharge from 11pm to 7am <br/>Personal expenses<br/>Round-trip transfers from hotels and resorts located outside the city center <br/>Round-trip transfers from the airport, sea/river ports, and train stations located inside or outside of the city center <br/><br/><b>Additional Info:</b><br/>Confirmation will be received within 48 hours of booking, subject to availability<br/>Must be booked at least 2 weeks in advance<br/>Rates are not applicable during F1 Malaysia Grand Prix<br/>A minimum of 2 people per booking is required<br/>Transport&nbsp;from accommodations outside the city center and suburbs are NOT&nbsp;included;&nbsp;supplements will be applied<br/>Transport from Kuala Lumpur International Airport is NOT&nbsp;included;&nbsp;supplements will be applied', null, null, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1', null, '1', '', '', null, '', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '', '', '2017-02-21 12:08:21', '6', '2017-02-21 12:16:44', '6', 'default');
INSERT INTO `product` VALUES ('126', '', 'https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/tly-production/partner_offers/images/000/005/561/medium/half-day-kuala-lumpur-city-tour-in-kuala-lumpur-245511.jpg?1450679473', '', '5561', 'Half-Day Kuala Lumpur City Tour', 'Enjoy this wonderful city tour that will give you approximately 4-hours of sightseeing around the fascinating city of Kuala Lumpur. Landmarks you will get to see include the National Monument, the King\'s Palace, the National Mosque and more. A great way to learn your way around the city and see some of the key attractions in a safe and exciting environment.', 'Your day will begin with a pickup from you hotel lobby at your chosen time slot. From here, you will be taken away in a fully air-conditioned vehicle to see the sites of Kuala Lumpur. Begin by visiting the National Monument that has exhibits of local history, culture and traditions, arts and crafts and a great bronze sculpture erected to commemorate the soldiers who lost their lives during World War II and the Emergency.<br /><br />You will then make a quick photo-stop at the gate of the King\'s Palace. From here, you\'ll proceed to the Moorish-style railway station building and the National Mosque, before finally arriving at the imposing Kuala Lumpur Tower. It is the highest tower in Asia and the fourth tallest telecommunications tower in the world.<br /><br />A drive past the elegant Jamek Mosque, the impressive House of Parliament and the world’s tallest twin towers, the Petronas Twin Towers is also a must. It has all the ingredients to hold the most avid travelers in amazement. Finally, you will be dropped back to your hotel.<br/><br/><b>Departure Time</b>: 9am or 2pm<br/><br/><b>Departure Point</b>: Your hotel in Kuala Lumpur<br/><br/><b>Operations</b>: Daily<br/><br/><b>Vourcher</b>: You can present either a paper or an electronic voucher for this activity.<br/><br/><b>Excerpt</b>: Enjoy this wonderful city tour that will give you approximately 4-hours of sightseeing around the fascinating city of Kuala Lumpur. Landmarks you will get to see include the National Monument, the...<br/><br/><b>Inclusions:</b><br/>Driver/guide<br/>Hotel pickup and drop-off<br/>Fuel surcharge<br/>GST (Goods and Services Tax)<br/>Local taxes<br/><br/><b>Exclusions:</b><br/>Entrance fees (any).<br/>Food and drinks<br/>Gratuities (optional)<br/>Souvenir photos (available to purchase)<br/><br/><b>Additional Info:</b><br/>Confirmation will be received at time of booking', null, null, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1', null, '1', '', '', null, '', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '', '', '2017-02-21 12:08:21', '6', '2017-02-21 12:16:44', '6', 'default');
INSERT INTO `product` VALUES ('127', '', 'https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/tly-production/partner_offers/images/000/003/011/medium/private-tour-half-day-batu-caves-tour-in-kuala-lumpur-190829.jpg?1487621746', '', '3011', 'Half Day Batu Caves Tour', 'Start your excursion with the visit of the Malaysian Batik Cottage as well as a short stop at the Royal Selangor Pewter factory. You will then proceed to the well-known Batu Caves, which has 272 steps to reach the shrine of the Hindu deity Lord Subramaniam and set within an outcrop of lime stone caves.', 'Start your excursion with the visit of the Malaysian Batik Cottage as well as a short stop at the Royal Selangor Pewter factory. You will then proceed to the well-known Batu Caves, which has 272 steps to reach the shrine of the Hindu deity Lord Subramaniam and set within an outcrop of lime stone caves. <br /><br />The main Hindu festivals are celebrated every year at Batu Cave including “Diwali” or Deepavali, that celebrate the victory of light over darkness; and also since 1892, the festival of Thaipusam, one of the biggest celebration for Hinduism community from all over the world. During Thaipusam, the procession of the event actually begins from a Temple (\"Maha Mariamman\" Temple, the oldest one in Kuala Lumpur built in 1873) located in the city center of Kuala Lumpur, barely a street behind the ever busy China Town. <br /><br />Batu cave remains the most interesting place outside of India to get a chance to observe and attend to the main celebrations of the Hindu community from India, Australia or Singapore. Hinduism remains a minority religion in Malaysia. An estimated 9% of the total population of Malaysia are ethnic Indians, of whom almost 89% are practicing Hinduism. Indian settlers came to Malaysia in the late 19th and early 20th centuries. Many of these came to work as laborers on rubber plantations, while those who were English-educated occupied more professional positions. <br /><br />This visit is not only a great opportunity to discover more about Hinduism traditions and beliefs, It is also a unique way to learn about the history of Malaysia and understand its multiculturalism.<br/><br/><b>Departure Time</b>: 9am<br />2pm<br/><br/><b>Departure Point</b>: Centrally located Kuala Lumpur hotels only<br/><br/><b>Operations</b>: Daily<br/><br/><b>Vourcher</b>: You can present either a paper or an electronic voucher for this activity.<br/><br/><b>Excerpt</b>: Start your excursion with the visit of the Malaysian Batik Cottage as well as a short stop at the Royal Selangor Pewter factory. You will then proceed to the well-known Batu Caves, which has 272...<br/><br/><b>Inclusions:</b><br/>Entrance fees<br/>Hotel pickup and drop-off<br/>Driver/guide only (supplement for separate guide apply and are subject to availability)<br/><br/><b>Exclusions:</b><br/>Gratuities (recommended)<br/>Separate guide for this tour (supplements apply)<br/>Surcharges per tour for pickup and drop-off other than from city hotels (e.g. Cititel Mid Valley, The Gardens, Boulevard, Hilton Kuala Lumpur at KL Sentral, Le Meridien, etc.)<br/>Transfers from and to airport, sea/river ports (such as the Port Klang Cruise terminal), train stations that are located inside or outside of the city center and others are NOT included in the service and supplements will applied.<br/>Transfers from and to hotels and resorts that are located outside of the city center are NOT included in the service and supplements will applied.<br/>Supplements apply during Malaysian Public Holidays<br/><br/><b>Additional Info:</b><br/>Confirmation will be received at time of booking<br/>Infant rates apply provided they do not occupy a seat<br/>Child rate applies only when sharing with 2 paying adults<br/>A minimum of 2 people per booking is required<br/>All tour pickups are from Kuala Lumpur city hotels only. A surcharge will be imposed for pick-up other than from city hotels<br/>Hotel pickup and drop-off at centrally located hotels only. A surcharge per tour will be imposed for pickup other than from city hotels (such as Cititel Midvalley, The Gardens, Boulevard, Hilton Kuala Lumpur at KL Sentral, Le Meridien, etc.). Confirmations of surcharges for hotels will be advised upon confirmation of hotel pickup and drop-off<br/>To enter the Batu Caves, customers are required to follow a certain dress code. This religious site does not allow customers entering the caves wearing short skirts / shorts that do not cover the knees or sleeveless shirts / tops. &nbsp;<br/>Supplements apply during Malaysian Public Holidays', null, null, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1', null, '1', '', '', null, '', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '', '', '2017-02-21 12:08:24', '6', '2017-02-21 12:16:47', '6', 'default');
INSERT INTO `product` VALUES ('128', '', 'https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/tly-production/partner_offers/images/000/003/012/medium/kuala-lumpur-city-tour-in-kuala-lumpur-219568.jpg?1450679468', '', '3012', 'Kuala Lumpur City Tour', 'A must for first time visitors to Kuala Lumpur. An interesting tour which unveils the beauty and charm of the old and new Kuala Lumpur. See the contrast of the magnificent skyscrapers and the buildings of the former colonial days.', 'Kuala Lumpur is a busy city with ordered skyscrapers, six-lane highways, colonial architecture and lots of greenery. Home to the Petronas Twin Towers, it is a shopping paradise with some of Southeast Asia’s largest shopping malls, housing the world’s top brands, and street markets where you can get one-of-a-kind items.<br />For any Chocolate fan a must visit is Cocoa Boutique where their products are unique and creative. You can purchase the usual chocolates of milk, white or dark chocolates but if you want something with Malaysian touch, this is the right place to go.<br/><br/><b>Departure Time</b>: Morning Departure: 8:45am - 9:15am<br />Afternoon Departure: 1:45pm - 2:15pm<br/><br/><b>Departure Point</b>: Your centrally located hotel in Kuala Lumpur<br/><br/><b>Operations</b>: Daily<br/><br/><b>Vourcher</b>: You can present either a paper or an electronic voucher for this activity.<br/><br/><b>Excerpt</b>: A must for first time visitors to Kuala Lumpur. An interesting tour which unveils the beauty and charm of the old and new Kuala Lumpur. See the contrast of the magnificent skyscrapers and the...<br/><br/><b>Inclusions:</b><br/>Hotel pick-up and drop-off in Kuala Lumpur<br/>Driver/guide<br/>Transport by air-conditioned minivan<br/><br/><b>Exclusions:</b><br/>Gratuities (optional)<br/>Entrance fee to National Museum<br/>Pick-up &amp; drop-off transfer from outside central Kuala Lumpur requires a surcharge of RM60.00 payable directly to the driver for your collection of receipt<br/><br/><b>Additional Info:</b><br/>Confirmation will be received at time of booking<br/>A minimum of 2 people per booking is required<br/>A maximum of 7 people per booking is allowed<br/>Infants free of charge, no seat<br/>Coach Tour', null, null, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1', null, '1', '', '', null, '', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '', '', '2017-02-21 12:08:25', '6', '2017-02-21 12:16:47', '6', 'default');
INSERT INTO `product` VALUES ('129', '', 'https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/tly-production/partner_offers/images/000/003/013/medium/malaysian-cultural-night-in-kuala-lumpur-in-kuala-lumpur-214804.jpg?1487621760', '', '3013', 'Malaysian Cultural Night in Kuala Lumpur', 'Inspired by Malaysia’s rich and exotic heritage, this 3.5-hour guided tour not only showcases the country’s abundant allure and beauty, but also showcases its ancient traditions mingled with cosmopolitan appeal. The tour kicks off with a visit to the vivacious Chinatown, known to locals as Petaling Street, this avenue plays host to plethora of vendors selling fruits, merchants peddling fake label goods and hawker stalls selling local delicacies.', 'After an evening pickup from your centrally located hotel, this evening tour takes you to the open air bazaar of ChinaTown, a Hindu Temple and a sumptuous Malay cuisine accompanied with a cultural show. At the first stop, the Sri Maha Mariamman Hindu Temple, the smell of burning jasmine, incessant chantings of Hindu priests and intricate carved deities combine to give a real mystical aura and a lasting impression of this religion. We then head to the Open Air Bazaar of Chinatown, take a stroll through this night market, where the locals engage in hectic bargaining for merchandises spread across the streets.<br /><br /> After, proceed to a Malay restaurant for buffet dinner and cultural show. Help yourself to a buffet dinner where a sumptuous variety of local dishes and delicacies await you. Be taken back to your accommodations afterward.<br/><br/><b>Departure Time</b>: 6:15pm - 6:30 pm<br/><br/><b>Departure Point</b>: Your centrally located Kuala Lumpur hotel<br/><br/><b>Operations</b>: Daily<br/><br/><b>Vourcher</b>: You can present either a paper or an electronic voucher for this activity.<br/><br/><b>Excerpt</b>: Inspired by Malaysia’s rich and exotic heritage, this 3.5-hour guided tour not only showcases the country’s abundant allure and beauty, but also showcases its ancient traditions mingled with...<br/><br/><b>Inclusions:</b><br/>Buffet dinner<br/>Driver/guide<br/>Hotel pickup and drop-off from city center<br/><br/><b>Exclusions:</b><br/>Personal expenses<br/>Gratuities (optional)<br/>For pickup and drop-off transfer from outside city center hotels a surcharge of RM60.00 will apply (please pay to driver and collect receipt)<br/><br/><b>Additional Info:</b><br/>Confirmation will be received at time of booking<br/>Infants free of charge, no seat<br/>A minimum of 2 people per booking is required<br/>Shorts , sleeveless shirt and slippers are not allowed<br/>Coach Tour', null, null, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1', null, '1', '', '', null, '', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '', '', '2017-02-21 12:08:26', '6', '2017-02-21 12:16:48', '6', 'default');
INSERT INTO `product` VALUES ('130', '', 'https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/tly-production/partner_offers/images/000/003/014/medium/kuala-lumpur-cultural-and-heritage-tour-in-kuala-lumpur-219807.jpg?1450679471', '', '3014', 'Kuala Lumpur Cultural and Heritage Tour', 'This tour will take you through the Heritage Trails of the early cultures in Malaysia and give you a great insight into Malaysia’s multi–cultural society', 'Apart from the modern sky scrapers in town, there are quite a number of beautiful Heritage Buildings which remain from the British Colonial days that still stand strong in the city. By exploring on foot, you can see many of these buildings that are in the older areas of Kuala Lumpur. Starting at the Central Market (Art-Deco), you can walk towards Independence Square or Dataran Merdeka where the Sultan Abdul Samad Building (SAS) stands majestically and is the largest of the heritage buildings here. Opposite, the English Tudor styled Royal Selangor Club sits facing the SAS Building. Head on over to the old railway station to see a couple more of the Neo Moorish and Mughal designed buildings. In the old city area, many shop houses don the old pre-war structures where you get to see a mix of influences in designs from Grecian-Spanish, neo-Gothic, Victorian and even the American styles that range from 1880s till 1950s.<br/><br/><b>Departure Time</b>: 9:30am<br/><br/><b>Departure Point</b>: Your centrally located Kuala Lumpur hotel<br/><br/><b>Operations</b>: Daily<br/><br/><b>Vourcher</b>: You can present either a paper or an electronic voucher for this activity.<br/><br/><b>Excerpt</b>: This tour will take you through the Heritage Trails of the early cultures in Malaysia and give you a great insight into Malaysia’s multi–cultural society<br/><br/><b>Inclusions:</b><br/>Hotel pickup and drop-off by air-conditioned minivan<br/>Driver/guide<br/>Coach tour<br/><br/><b>Exclusions:</b><br/>Gratuities (optional)<br/><br/><b>Additional Info:</b><br/>Confirmation will be received at time of booking<br/>Infants free of charge, no seat<br/>A minimum of 2 people per booking is required<br/>All transfers and half/full day tours – NO refund for cancellation received within 24 hours notice<br/>Note: Not available during Chinese New Year Festival', null, null, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1', null, '1', '', '', null, '', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '', '', '2017-02-21 12:08:26', '6', '2017-02-21 12:16:49', '6', 'default');
INSERT INTO `product` VALUES ('131', '', 'https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/tly-production/offers/images/000/003/021/medium/5D_Orion_Simulator_02.jpg?1439960714', '', '3021', '5D Orion Simulator Ride at Berjaya Times Square Theme Park', 'Transport yourself into a new dimension as you board the 5D Orion Simulator! This unique ride allows you to be an interactive gamer as you take on missions with the use of your joystick. An adventure that is suitable for anyone, adults or children!', 'A 3D video coupled with surrounding environment simulation will provide for an exciting ride through an interactive simulated reality. As you step into the 4-seater spacecraft-like 5D Orion, you will take on the role of a gamer with 3D glasses and individual joysticks awaiting you. With its stereo image system and 180-degrees wide-ranging Stereoscopic 3D screen, you can be assured of an exhilarating gaming experience. \r\n\r\nOnce inside, you will be able to choose from a range of 15 gaming missions which includes amusement rides, shooters, kids rides, speedboats and tank simulators.  As you begin, your mission will be given to you and so, prepare to shoot, dodge, swerve, fly and much more as you complete your mission. Throughout the simulation, you will experience a full motion platform with 6 degrees of freedom, producing vertical, horizontal, longitudinal, transverse and rotary motions based on your control of the joystick, leaving you with a full body experience.\r\n\r\nSo, what are you waiting for? Do some time traveling, fight robots and monsters, visit another planet or be a tank soldier! A whole different world awaits you!<br/><br/><b>Departure Time</b>: Operating Hours: 12 pm – 10 pm<br/><br/><b>Departure Point</b>: Location: ￼5th Floor, Berjaya Times Square, Jalan Imbi, 55100 Kuala Lumpur.<br/><br/><b>Operations</b>: Daily<br/><br/><b>Vourcher</b>: You must present a paper certificate for this activity. Please present your certificate at the 5D Simulator Ride ticket counter for admission.<br/><br/><b>Excerpt</b>: Transport yourself into a new dimension as you board the 5D Orion Simulator! This unique ride allows you to be an interactive gamer as you take on missions with the use of your joystick. An...<br/><br/><b>Inclusions:</b><br/>Admission for 5D Simulator Ride<br/>Use of 3D glasses<br/><br/><b>Exclusions:</b><br/>Hotel pickup and drop-off<br/>Food and beverages, unless specified<br/>Gratuities (optional)<br/><br/><b>Additional Info:</b><br/>Complete operator information, including local telephone numbers at your destination, are included on your certificate.<br/>Prior booking is not required.<br/>Adult pricing applies to  all travellers.<br/>Minimum age is 3 years.', null, null, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', null, null, '1', '', '', null, '', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '', '', '2017-02-21 12:08:27', '6', '2017-02-21 12:16:49', '6', 'default');
INSERT INTO `product` VALUES ('132', '', 'https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/tly-production/partner_offers/images/000/006/863/medium/half-day-private-kuala-lumpur-city-tour-in-kuala-lumpur-292257.jpg?1458073692', '', '6863', 'Half-Day Private Kuala Lumpur City Tour', 'Explore Kuala Lumpur\'s major attractions on a private, half-day tour. You\'ll see the Royal King’s Palace (Istana Negara), Old Railway Station, Perdana Botanical Garden (aka Lake Gardens), and National Mosque (Masjid Negara). Select a morning departure or an afternoon tour, including round-trip hotel transport with your personal guide.', 'Start your 3-hour, private tour with hotel pickup in central Kuala Lumpur. Your personal driver and guide take you to Chinatown for an introduction to its three parallel streets, best known for street food and places of worship. Then learn about the residential neighborhood of Brickfields while exploring the oldest Indian settlement in KL.<br /><br />Stop for photo ops of the royal guards and mounted guards at Istana Negara, aka the Royal King\'s Palace — official residence of the ruler of Malaysia. View the National Monument that commemorates the fallen heroes of World War I and II, then set off for the Perdana Botanical Garden for a drive or stroll through the butterfly farm, bird park, orchid garden, hibiscus garden and more.<br /><br />Your guide also accompanies you to Masjid Negara, the National Mosque officiated in1965, After you visit, take note of the Old Railway Station built in 1911. Explore this architectural wonder then see Merdeka Square bordered by the Sultan Abdul Samad building, Royal Selangor Club, and St. Mary\'s Cathedral.<br /><br />Visit the Jadi Batek Gallery, a batik handicraft center that showcases Malaysia\'s traditional garment, and discover many varieties of chocolate at the Cocoa Boutique. After these sights you\'re dropped off at your hotel in central Kuala Lumpur.<br/><br/><b>Departure Time</b>: 9am<br />2pm<br/><br/><b>Departure Point</b>: Your hotel in central Kuala Lumpur<br/><br/><b>Operations</b>: Daily<br/><br/><b>Vourcher</b>: You can present either a paper or an electronic voucher for this activity.<br/><br/><b>Excerpt</b>: Explore Kuala Lumpur\'s major attractions on a private, half-day tour. You\'ll see the Royal King’s Palace (Istana Negara), Old Railway Station, Perdana Botanical Garden (aka Lake Gardens), and...<br/><br/><b>Inclusions:</b><br/>Private driver and vehicle<br/>Professional guide<br/>Hotel pickup and drop-off in Kuala Lumpur city<br/>Fuel surcharge<br/><br/><b>Exclusions:</b><br/>Entrance fees<br/>Food and beverages<br/><br/><b>Additional Info:</b><br/>Confirmation will be received at time of booking<br/>Children must be accompanied by an adult<br/>Please wear comfortable walking shoes', null, null, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1', null, '1', '', '', null, '', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '', '', '2017-02-21 12:08:28', '6', '2017-02-21 12:16:50', '6', 'default');
INSERT INTO `product` VALUES ('133', '', 'https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/tly-production/offers/images/000/003/025/medium/Picture_27.png?1440248437', '', '3025', 'Full Day Wild River Tubing Tour from Kuala Lumpur', 'Enjoy a different perspective of the wild jungle, not by foot but through the river! Join in on an exciting river tubing experience as you free float down the jungle river for a day of continuous fun, fun and fun!', 'After a hotel pickup, you will make your way towards the lush Malaysian jungle, located in Kuala Kubu Bharu, Hulu Selangor. This jungle is a part of the Titiwangsa mountain range, the remaining continuous forested stretch in Peninsula Malaysia. \r\n\r\nOnce there, your day\'s river adventure starts with a safety briefing and an equipment fitting session. Then, the excitement begins! Get onto your inner tube and prepare to ride down the jungle river spanning 2.5 kilometres long. Free float and  manoeuvre past rapids of all kinds and get ready for water splashing at you from all sides. The rides range from 1.5 to 2 hours to ensure maximum fun and if you’re lucky, the river otters may also come out to play and enjoy too.\r\n\r\n**Good to Note:** <ul><li> Please wear comfortable walking shoes and bring swimwear, towel, change of clothes, sunscreen and insect repellent.</li><br/><br/><b>Departure Time</b>: 7 am<br/><br/><b>Departure Point</b>: Tour departs from Kuala Lumpur city centre and Petaling Jaya hotels.<br/><br/><b>Operations</b>: Daily<br/><br/><b>Vourcher</b>: You can present either a paper or an electronic certificate for this activity.<br/><br/><b>Excerpt</b>: Enjoy a different perspective of the wild jungle, not by foot but through the river! Join in on an exciting river tubing experience as you free float down the jungle river for a day of continuous...<br/><br/><b>Inclusions:</b><br/>Hotel pickup and drop-off<br/>Local English-speaking guide<br/>Breakfast<br/>Lunch<br/>Use of safety helmets, Personal Floatation Device and river tubing shoes<br/><br/><b>Exclusions:</b><br/>Gratuities (optional)<br/><br/><b>Additional Info:</b><br/><b>After your purchase on Touristly is confirmed, complete your booking by emailing <a href=\"mailto:chen@primalcreations.com\">chen@primalcreations.com</a> with the following details:</b><ul><li>Lead traveller name and contact number</li><li>Number of passengers</li><li>Preferred tour date</li><li>Touristly certificate as booking reference</li><li>Hotel accommodation</li></ul><br/>Booking is essential and must be made at least 7 days prior to intended tour date to avoid disappointment.<br/>Confirmation by the local operator will be received within 48 hours from when booking is made, subject to availability.<br/>Complete operator information, including local telephone numbers at your destination, are included on your certificate.<br/>Minimum age is 8 years.<br/>A minimum of 2 people per booking is required.<br/>A maximum of 10 people per booking is allowed.<br/>Adult pricing applies to all travellers.<br/>Subject to favorable weather conditions. If canceled due to poor weather, you will be given the option of an alternative date or full refund.<br/><b>Cancellation Policy:</b> Cancellations made at least 3 days prior to scheduled departure is fully refundable. Cancellations made 2 days or less prior to scheduled departure incurs a 100% cancellation fee.', null, null, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', null, null, '1', '', '', null, '', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '', '', '2017-02-21 12:08:28', '6', '2017-02-21 12:16:51', '6', 'default');
INSERT INTO `product` VALUES ('134', '', 'https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/tly-production/offers/images/000/003/026/medium/IMG_9013.jpg?1443524961', '', '3026', 'Full Day River and Jungle Trekking Tour from Kuala Lumpur', 'Take a break from the bustling city and escape for a day to fresh air, cool waters and flourishing trees. The Malaysian jungle is a tropical paradise and has much to offer with its many waterfalls and abundant flora and fauna. It is truly a hidden gem waiting to be unearthed by you!', 'The tour kicks off after your hotel pickup, heading towards and into the dense and lush Malaysian jungle, teeming with flora. If you\'re in luck, you might also encounter some wild animals along the way. The jungle situated in Kuala Kubu Bharu, is part of the Titiwangsa mountain range, Peninsular Malaysia\'s largest continuous forest tract left.  With an experienced guide, you will trek through river crossings, scramble over rocks and boulders and crawl through bamboo thickets. It is a jungle that is full of bubbling creeks with a slightly hilly terrain, making the trek an easy one for anyone and everyone. \r\n\r\nOn this tour, be treated to the serene landscape changes surrounding you and glimpses of the scenic mountain ranges as you make your way deeper into this tropical paradise. You will also come across numerous waterfalls, small and big but refreshing all the same. End the trek at a majestic multi-tiered waterfall where the group will stop for a picnic lunch. You will have the opportunity to walk into the falls, through a thunderous curtain of water pouring over you and enter inside a small rocky promontory, slightly hidden away. Have a rest, give your body a break and enjoy the relaxing environment around you.\r\n\r\n**Good to Note:** <ul><li> Please wear comfortable walking shoes and bring swimwear, towel, change of clothes, sunscreen and insect repellent.</li><br/><br/><b>Departure Time</b>: 7 am<br/><br/><b>Departure Point</b>: Tour departs from Kuala Lumpur city centre and Petaling Jaya hotels.<br/><br/><b>Operations</b>: Monday – Friday<br/><br/><b>Vourcher</b>: You can present either a paper or an electronic certificate for this activity.<br/><br/><b>Excerpt</b>: Take a break from the bustling city and escape for a day to fresh air, cool waters and flourishing trees. The Malaysian jungle is a tropical paradise and has much to offer with its many waterfalls...<br/><br/><b>Inclusions:</b><br/>Hotel pickup and drop-off<br/>Local English-speaking guide<br/>Breakfast<br/>Lunch<br/>Dinner<br/><br/><b>Exclusions:</b><br/>Gratuities (optional)<br/><br/><b>Additional Info:</b><br/><b>After your purchase on Touristly is confirmed, complete your booking by emailing <a href=\"mailto:chen@primalcreations.com\">chen@primalcreations.com</a> with the following details:</b><ul><li>Lead traveller name and contact number</li><li>Number of passengers</li><li>Preferred tour date</li><li>Touristly certificate number as booking reference</li><li>Hotel accommodation</li></ul><br/>Booking is essential and must be made at least 7 days prior to intended tour date to avoid disappointment.<br/>Confirmation by the local operator will be received within 48 hours from when booking is made, subject to availability.<br/>Complete operator information, including local telephone numbers at your destination, are included on your certificate.<br/>Minimum age is 8 years.<br/>A minimum of 2 people per booking is required.<br/>A maximum of 10 people per booking is allowed<br/>Adult pricing applies to all travellers.<br/>Subject to favorable weather conditions. If canceled due to poor weather, you will be given the option of an alternative date or full refund.<br/><b>Cancellation Policy:</b> Cancellations made at least 3 days prior to scheduled departure is fully refundable. Cancellations made 2 days or less prior to scheduled departure incurs a 100% cancellation fee.', null, null, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', null, null, '1', '', '', null, '', null