erson<br/>Hotel drop-off<br/><br/><b>Exclusions:</b><br/>Gratuities (optional)<br/>Excess luggage charges (where applicable)<br/><br/><b>Additional Info:</b><br/>Confirmation will be received at time of booking<br/>Child rate applies only when sharing with 2 paying adults.<br/>Infant rates apply provided they do not occupy a seat.<br/>Vehicle does not specifically cater to passenger traveling with wheelchair. However, collapsible wheelchairs can be&nbsp;accommodated providing the passenger is accompanied by someone who can assist them to board and disembark.<br/>A minimum of 2 people per booking is required', null, null, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1', null, '1', '', '', null, '', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '', '', '2017-02-21 12:09:44', '6', '2017-02-21 12:18:00', '6', 'default');
INSERT INTO `product` VALUES ('203', '', 'https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/tly-production/partner_offers/images/000/008/100/medium/shared-departure-transfer-hotel-to-kuala-lumpur-international-airport-in-kuala-lumpur-320717.jpg?1487621748', '', '8100', 'Shared Departure Transfer: Hotel to Kuala Lumpur International Airport', 'Pre-book your hassle-free departure transfer to Kuala Lumpur International Airport (KLIA) or Kuala Lumpur International Airport 2 (KLIA2, low cost carrier terminal), enjoy a comfortable shared transfer in an air-conditioned minivan with English-speaking driver cum guide.', 'Pre-book your hassle-free departure transfer to Kuala Lumpur International Airport (KLIA) or Kuala Lumpur International Airport 2 (KLIA2, low cost carrier terminal), enjoy a comfortable shared transfer in an air-conditioned minivan with English-speaking driver cum guide. The driver will pick you up from the hotel you are staying and transfer you directly to the airport. <br /><br />When reserving your shared transfer, please provide your departure flight details and hotel information (hotel name and location). You will receive instant confirmation for your booking and a voucher will be emailed to you. Please present your voucher to the driver during transfer pick-up. The departure transfer is available 24 hours a day, seven days a week.<br/><br/><b>Departure Time</b>: Flexible<br/><br/><b>Departure Point</b>: Your hotel lobby/main entrance<br/><br/><b>Operations</b>: <p>Daily</p><br/><br/><b>Vourcher</b>: You can present either a paper or an electronic voucher for this activity.<br/><br/><b>Excerpt</b>: Pre-book your hassle-free departure transfer to Kuala Lumpur International Airport (KLIA) or Kuala Lumpur International Airport 2 (KLIA2, low cost carrier terminal), enjoy a comfortable shared...<br/><br/><b>Inclusions:</b><br/>One-way shared transfer<br/>All applicable local taxes<br/>Hotel pickup<br/><br/><b>Exclusions:</b><br/>Gratuities (optional)<br/>Excess luggage charges (where applicable)<br/><br/><b>Additional Info:</b><br/>Confirmation will be received at time of booking<br/>Child rate applies only when sharing with 2 paying adults<br/>Infant rates apply provided they do not occupy a seat.<br/>Vehicle does not specifically cater to passenger traveling with wheelchair. However, collapsible wheelchairs can be&nbsp;accommodated providing the passenger is accompanied by someone who can assist them to board and disembark.<br/>A maximum of 2 people per booking<br/>Hotel pickups commence according to agreed timing, exact pickup time will be advised 24 hrs before departure day. Departure from city centre hotels: 3 hours before flight departure time', null, null, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1', null, '1', '', '', null, '', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '', '', '2017-02-21 12:09:44', '6', '2017-02-21 12:18:01', '6', 'default');
INSERT INTO `product` VALUES ('204', '', 'https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/tly-production/partner_offers/images/000/008/103/medium/private-half-day-kuala-lumpur-photographic-tour-including-tickets-to-in-kuala-lumpur-320747.jpg?1461269764', '', '8103', 'Private Half-Day Kuala Lumpur Photographic Tour Including Tickets to Petronas Twin Towers and KL Tower', '<p>Admire the picturesque sights of Kuala Lumpur while photographing some of its most iconic landmarks. This full-day private tour covers the scenic views from the top of Petronas Twin Towers and Kuala Lumpur Tower. Focus your camera on the Old Railway Station, Merdeka Square, and Thean Hou Temple while sightseeing with your driver.</p>', '<p>Prepare for a half day filled with photographic opportunities as you start your tour with hotel pickup in the morning or afternoon. Your driver takes you to the Petronas Twin Towers, where your admission ticket gives you access to the Observation Deck and Skybridge. From here, see the city skyscrapers, palaces, and museums shimmering in the sunlight.</p>\r\n<p>Next on your itinerary is the King’s Palace, or Istana Negara, which hundreds of photographers visit each year. Capture the magnificent beauty of the complex\'s opulent architecture that includes 22 domes. You also have the opportunity to take some pictures of modern buildings mixed in with colonial masterpieces in the center of Merdeka (Independence) Square, one of the architectural jewels of Kuala Lumpur.<br /><br />Take a break from the hustle and bustle at the Lake Gardens, where you can wander the trails of the manicured park. Don’t forget to photograph the picturesque Orchid Gardens and the National Monument, located nearby. Stop by the Old Railway Station to snap pictures of intricate details in the arcs, verandas, and vast balconies designed by colonial architects.<br /><br />Continue on to KL Tower, which rises high above the city. Climb the staircase or ascend by elevator to a height of 1,381 feet (421 meters) and note its glass dome. After soaking up the panoramic view, pay a visit to Thean Hou Temple, whose red pillars, dragons, and prayer rooms reflect an eclectic mixture of Taoism, Buddhism and Confucianism. The temple is dedicated to the Goddess of Mercy, and its shrine and sculptures represent the animals of the Chinese Zodiac. </p>\r\n<p>Your personalized tour comes to an end with private transport back to your hotel.</p><br/><br/><b>Departure Time</b>: 9am<br /> 2pm<br/><br/><b>Departure Point</b>: Your hotel in Kuala Lumpur or Petaling Jaya<br/><br/><b>Operations</b>: Daily except Monday<br/><br/><b>Vourcher</b>: You can present either a paper or an electronic voucher for this activity.<br/><br/><b>Excerpt</b>: Admire the picturesque sights of Kuala Lumpur while photographing some of its most iconic landmarks. This full-day private tour covers the scenic views from the top of Petronas Twin Towers...<br/><br/><b>Inclusions:</b><br/>Entrance tickets to Petronas Twin Towers and KLTower<br/>Professional driver/guide<br/>Hotel pickup and drop-off<br/><br/><b>Exclusions:</b><br/>Personal expenses<br/>Food and beverages<br/><br/><b>Additional Info:</b><br/>Confirmation will be received at time of booking<br/>The tour and itinerary may change without prior notice due to unforeseen circumstances. You will be advised of the change as soon as possible or receive a full refund.<br/>A minimum of 2 people per booking is required', null, null, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1', null, '1', '', '', null, '', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '', '', '2017-02-21 12:09:45', '6', '2017-02-21 12:18:02', '6', 'default');
INSERT INTO `product` VALUES ('205', '', 'https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/tly-production/partner_offers/images/000/008/106/medium/half-day-shopping-and-market-exploration-tour-in-kuala-lumpur-in-kuala-lumpur-320743.jpg?1461356160', '', '8106', 'Half-Day Shopping and Market Exploration Tour in Kuala Lumpur', '<p>Let a driver/guide introduce you to Kuala Lumpur’s biggest markets and bustling streets filled with vendors, restaurants, and shops. Immerse yourself in the bazaars of Chinatown and Little India (Jalan Masjid India) where you\'ll find Malay, Chinese, and Indian cuisine. Have time to browse and bargain independently for high-quality goods, including at Central Market. Hotel pickup and drop-off is included on this half-day tour in the morning or afternoon.</p>', 'Your half-day tour begins with pickup your hotel in Kuala Lumpur or Petaling Jaya. Your driver will provide a general briefing about the places visited, but will not accompany you from into the markets, which you\'ll explore on your own.<br /><br />First, head to Chinatown where you can stroll the streets and shop alleyways packed with food stalls selling a wide range of foods and local goods. Once you\'ve mastered the art of negotiating for bargains, your tour continues to Brickfields, also known as Little India, one of the oldest settlements in Malaysia. Explore the colorful streets and Indian shops where you can purchase saris, flower garlands, and delicious <em>dosa</em> (Indian pancakes).<br /><br />After tasting and shopping in Little India, move on to Central Market (Pasar Seni), another indoor bazaar not far from Chinatown. The spacious market offers a variety of foods and distinctive souvenirs along with traditional Malaysian goods. After experiencing the local ambience, you will be transported back to your hotel in an air-conditioned vehicle.<br/><br/><b>Departure Time</b>: 10am or 2pm<br/><br/><b>Departure Point</b>: Your hotel in Kuala Lumpur or Petaling Jaya<br/><br/><b>Operations</b>: Daily<br/><br/><b>Vourcher</b>: You can present either a paper or an electronic voucher for this activity.<br/><br/><b>Excerpt</b>: Let a driver/guide introduce you to Kuala Lumpur’s biggest markets and bustling streets filled with vendors, restaurants, and shops. Immerse yourself in the bazaars of Chinatown and Little India...<br/><br/><b>Inclusions:</b><br/>Professional driver<br/>Hotel pickup and drop-off<br/><br/><b>Exclusions:</b><br/>Food and beverages<br/>Personal expenses<br/>Guide <br/><br/><b>Additional Info:</b><br/>Confirmation will be received at time of booking<br/>Please note: driver will provide a general briefing about the places visited but will not accompany you from shop to shop in the market. You will have to bargain, shop and explore markets on your own.<br/>The tour and itinerary may change without prior notice due to unforeseen circumstances (if any). You will be advised of the change as soon as possible or receive a full refund.<br/>A minimum of 2 people per booking is required', null, null, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1', null, '1', '', '', null, '', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '', '', '2017-02-21 12:09:46', '6', '2017-02-21 12:18:03', '6', 'default');
INSERT INTO `product` VALUES ('206', '', 'https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/tly-production/offers/images/000/000/175/medium/Fiercer_Rati_rolls.jpg?1404186044', '', '175', 'Fiercer by Fierce Curry House, Publika', 'Fiercer is the bigger, more sophisticated sister of Fierce Curry House. The original outlet in Bangsar is a little more casual, opening out onto the street, while big sis is chic in design and brings some new things to the menu too.', 'Fierce Curry House, opened for only a year, quickly gained a reputation for making luxurious biryanis - think lobster, scallop and veal! Fiercer carries these famed dishes to Publika, but also adds booze, Kati Rolls (a popular Indian street food) and homemade ice cream by The Last Polka to its offerings.\r\n\r\nApparently original Kati Rolls came from Kolkata and were made with paratha bread encircling a kati kebab. Nowadays however, the name Kati Roll is generically used for just about any Indian flatbread that wraps up any number of fillings. Chefs at Fiercer cook up four versions: chicken; mutton; prawn and; vegetarian. This was our first experience with a kati roll so honestly we have nothing to compare it with. We found them to be spicy, tasty, filling snacks, likely to go down very well with a chilled beer. \r\n\r\n**Additional Details** \r\nD1-G3-5 Solaris Dutamas/ Publika\r\nJalan Solaris Dutamas 1\r\n50480 Kuala Lumpur\r\nMalaysia \r\n\r\nTel No: \r\n+6 03 6211 2066 \r\n\r\nMobile No:\r\n019 770 1945 \r\n\r\n(Source: http://theyumlist.blogspot.com/2014/01/fiercer-by-fierce-curry-house-publika.html) <br/><br/><b>Departure Time</b>: <br/><br/><b>Departure Point</b>: <br/><br/><b>Operations</b>: <br/><br/><b>Vourcher</b>: <br/><br/><b>Excerpt</b>: Fiercer is the bigger, more sophisticated sister of Fierce Curry House. The original outlet in Bangsar is a little more casual, opening out onto the street, while big sis is chic in design and...<br/><br/><b>Inclusions:</b><br/><br/><br/><b>Exclusions:</b><br/><br/><br/><b>Additional Info:</b><br/>', null, null, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', null, null, '1', '', '', null, '', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '', '', '2017-02-21 12:09:47', '6', '2017-02-21 12:18:04', '6', 'default');
