at time of booking if wheelchair assistance is required<br/>Minimum luggage per person 1 big bag plus 1 hand carry bag only<br/>Midnight surcharge 50% applicable for transfer made between 10pm-7am<br/>All transfers and half/full day tours – NO refund for cancellation received within 24 hours notice<br/>Passenger contact required<br/>Transfer is one-way', null, null, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1', null, '1', '', '', null, '', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '', '', '2017-02-21 12:09:48', '6', '2017-02-21 12:18:04', '6', 'default');
INSERT INTO `product` VALUES ('208', '', 'https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/tly-production/partner_offers/images/000/008/114/medium/one-way-low-cost-private-arrival-transfer-from-kuala-lumpur-in-kuala-lumpur-236276.jpg?1461615422', '', '8114', 'One-Way Low Cost Private Arrival Transfer from Kuala Lumpur International Airport to Kuala Lumpur City', '<p>Enjoy a private airport transfer from Kuala Lumpur International Airport (KUL) to Kuala Lumpur city. Avoid the lines for taxis and confusion caused by language barriers or public transportation.</p>', '<p>Sit back and relax while our driver leads you the way and assists you with your luggage. You will not have to worry about any details on how to get to your location in Kuala Lumpur.</p>\r\n<p>You will be awaited by your private driver in the arrival terminal holding in sign with your name on it. When your flight is delayed, do not worry, your driver will monitor your flight and be there when you arrived. He will then help you with your luggage and lead you to the car. Once you and the driver double-checked the location address you provided us with he will take you straight to your destination in Kuala Lumpur. Enjoy the drive past the famous Petronas Towers&nbsp;and the iconic Merdeka Square&nbsp;while the driver takes you to your destination.</p>\r\n<p>It is important that when you book you provide us your flight number and the address of destination in Kuala Lumpur to ensure that your trip proceeds without any problems. Once you booked you will receive a booking confirmation in the form of a travel voucher to present to your private driver.</p><br/><br/><b>Departure Time</b>: Flexible<br/><br/><b>Departure Point</b>: <p>Arrival Terminal at the Kuala Lumpur International Airport (KUL)</p><br/><br/><b>Operations</b>: <p>Daily</p><br/><br/><b>Vourcher</b>: You can present either a paper or an electronic voucher for this activity.<br/><br/><b>Excerpt</b>: Enjoy a private airport transfer from Kuala Lumpur International Airport (KUL) to Kuala Lumpur city. Avoid the lines for taxis and confusion caused by language barriers or public...<br/><br/><b>Inclusions:</b><br/>Meet and greet service (pick-up on arrival with name sign)<br/>One-way private transfer<br/>30 minute waiting time (in case of flight delay)<br/>1 luggage per person<br/>Hotel drop-off<br/><br/><b>Exclusions:</b><br/>Gratuities (optional)<br/>Excess luggage charges<br/>Delays over 30 minutes<br/><br/><b>Additional Info:</b><br/>Confirmation will be received within 48 hours of booking, subject to availability<br/>The exact duration will depend on the time of day and traffic conditions<br/>For oversized or excessive luggage (e.g. surfboards, golf clubs or bikes), please inquire prior to travel to confirm if your excess luggage is acceptable', null, null, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1', null, '1', '', '', null, '', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '', '', '2017-02-21 12:09:49', '6', '2017-02-21 12:18:05', '6', 'default');
INSERT INTO `product` VALUES ('209', '', 'https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/tly-production/partner_offers/images/000/008/115/medium/one-way-low-cost-private-arrival-transfer-from-kuala-lumpur-in-kuala-lumpur-236276.jpg?1461615424', '', '8115', 'One-Way Low Cost Private Arrival Transfer from Kuala Lumpur International Airport to Banting City', '<p>Low cost private taxi transfer from Kuala Lumpur International Airport (KUL) to your hotel or address in Banting city centre.</p>', '<p>Make sure everything for your trip is organized. Our driver will be there when you arrive and ensure your safe and fast transfer to Banting without you having to worry.</p>\r\n<p>You will be awaited by your private driver in the arrival terminal holding in sign with your name on it. When your flight is delayed, do not worry, your driver will monitor your flight and be there when you arrived. He will then help you with your luggage and lead you to the car. Once you and the driver double-checked the location address you provided us with he will take you straight to your destination in Banting. Enjoy the drive past the famous Morib Beach&nbsp;and the Tadom Base&nbsp;while the driver takes you to your destination.</p>\r\n<p>To make sure that your transfer progresses smoothly we ask you to provide us with your flight number and the address of destination in Banting when you confirm the booking. As soon as you booked you will receive a transfer voucher to present to your private driver.</p><br/><br/><b>Departure Time</b>: Flexible<br/><br/><b>Departure Point</b>: <p>Arrival Terminal at the Kuala Lumpur International Airport (KUL)</p><br/><br/><b>Operations</b>: <p>Daily</p><br/><br/><b>Vourcher</b>: You can present either a paper or an electronic voucher for this activity.<br/><br/><b>Excerpt</b>: Low cost private taxi transfer from Kuala Lumpur International Airport (KUL) to your hotel or address in Banting city centre.<br/><br/><b>Inclusions:</b><br/>Meet and greet service (pick-up on arrival with name sign)<br/>One-way private transfer<br/>30 minute waiting time (in case of flight delay)<br/>1 luggage per person<br/>Hotel drop-off<br/><br/><b>Exclusions:</b><br/>Gratuities (optional)<br/>Excess luggage charges<br/>Delays over 30 minutes<br/><br/><b>Additional Info:</b><br/>Confirmation will be received within 48 hours of booking, subject to availability<br/>The exact duration will depend on the time of day and traffic conditions<br/>For oversized or excessive luggage (e.g. surfboards, golf clubs or bikes), please inquire prior to travel to confirm if your excess luggage is acceptable', null, null, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1', null, '1', '', '', null, '', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '', '', '2017-02-21 12:09:49', '6', '2017-02-21 12:18:06', '6', 'default');
INSERT INTO `product` VALUES ('210', '', 'https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/tly-production/partner_offers/images/000/008/116/medium/one-way-low-cost-private-arrival-transfer-from-kuala-lumpur-in-kuala-lumpur-236276.jpg?1487621784', '', '8116', 'One-Way Private Arrival Transfer from Kuala Lumpur Airport to Port Dickson City', '<p>This private airport transfer takes you from Kuala Lumpur International Airport (KUL) to Port Dickson city. Avoid the lines for taxis and confusion caused by language barriers or public transportation.</p>', '<p>Enjoy the luxury of a private driver who brings you safely to Port Dickson. Avoid the stress of waiting in lines and the hassle of public transportation. Simply enter your flight details and the destination address when you book and pay in advance. You are supplied with a travel voucher that you can present to your private driver, who will monitor your flight in case of delay (30-minute allowance). </p>\r\n<p>Your driver will be waiting for you in the Arrivals Terminal holding a sign with your name on it. On arrival, you\'re assisted with your luggage and led to the car, then driven straight to your destination in Port Dickson. You may pass by the Tanjung Tuan Forest Reserve or Cape Rachado Lighthouse along the way.<br /><br />Price is per vehicle, based on five passengers per car.</p><br/><br/><b>Departure Time</b>: Depends on your flight\'s arrival<br/><br/><b>Departure Point</b>: <p>Arrival Terminal at the Kuala Lumpur International Airport (KUL)</p><br/><br/><b>Operations</b>: <p>Daily</p><br/><br/><b>Vourcher</b>: You can present either a paper or an electronic voucher for this activity.<br/><br/><b>Excerpt</b>: This private airport transfer takes you from Kuala Lumpur International Airport (KUL) to Port Dickson city. Avoid the lines for taxis and confusion caused by language barriers or public...<br/><br/><b>Inclusions:</b><br/>Meet-and-greet service (pickup on arrival with name sign)<br/>One-way private transfer<br/>30-minute waiting time allowed (in case of flight delay)<br/>1 luggage per person<br/>Hotel drop-off<br/><br/><b>Exclusions:</b><br/>Excess luggage charges<br/>Delays over 30 minutes<br/><br/><b>Additional Info:</b><br/>Confirmation will be received within 48 hours of booking, subject to availability<br/>The exact duration will depend on the time of day and traffic conditions<br/>For oversized or excessive luggage (e.g. surfboards, golf clubs or bikes), please inquire prior to travel to confirm if your excess luggage is acceptable', null, null, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1', null, '1', '', '', null, '', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '', '', '2017-02-21 12:09:50', '6', '2017-02-21 12:18:06', '6', 'default');
INSERT INTO `product` VALUES ('211', '', 'https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/tly-production/partner_offers/images/000/008/117/medium/private-kuala-lumpur-orientation-day-tour-in-kuala-lumpur-310922.jpg?1487621743', '', '8117', 'Private Kuala Lumpur Customize Orientation Full Day Tour', 'Join this full-day private tour exploring Kuala Lumpur lead by a professional English speaking driver/guide and get some local inside tips. This approximately 8 hours tour in Kuala Lumpur is a great opportunity to experience and learn the local lifestyle, history and culture which makes by multiple ethnic groups. There are two departure time for this tour, 9am and 12pm. You will be picked up by the driver at your hotel lobby at your chosen time slot.', 'You will be picked up from your hotel lobby located in Kuala Lumpur or Petaling Jaya and head to the Petronas Twin Towers building, a distinctive icon universally associated with Kuala Lumpur. The 88-floor towers have a facade of steel and glass that distinctly reflect images of Islamic Art. Designed by a South American architect, the base of Twin Towers houses a shopping mall and the Malaysian Philharmonic Orchestra. <br /><br />You will then visit Lake Gardens (Perdana Botanical Garden), with some beautiful trees, man-made waterfalls and playground. We will stop at a war memorial the National Monument. It is a huge bronze statue, muscular in nature, with warriors defending the wounded and fallen.<br />National Mosque (Masjid Negara), a magnificent structure that is a unique embodiment of modern Islamic art with stunning traditional elements. We will explore Kuala Lumpur Railway Station, a lovely majestic palace once nearby the National Mosque.<br /><br />Chinese Thean Hou Temple, built in the classic style of Mainland China. Being one of the oldest and greatest temples in Southeast Asia, this landmark attracts millions of tourists from across the globe each year.<br /><br />If you are more into shopping than sightseeing, you can easily omit any of these places and go for a fascinating journey into the depth of Central Market, where you can spend your time looking through artwork, souvenirs, and batik masterpieces. Chinatown, filled with countless Chinese shops is an ideal place to hunt for everything from cheap spices to gadgets. Little India is a small Indian island inside the bustling streets of Kuala Lumpur.&nbsp; Here you can try fantastic Indian dishes, look for bright saris and enjoy the glittery stalls filled with trinkets and jewelry of all kinds.<br /><br />The second most desired visiting place in Kuala Lumpur is the Batu Caves. Dedicated to Lord Murugan, this Hindu shrine holds a magnificent 155ft (47meter) statue erected in his honor. 272 stairs lead to the massive Temple Cave with a spectacular 328ft (100meter) high ceiling. The cave is filled with statues of Hindu gods and intricate paintings illuminated by the holes in the rock of the ceiling.<br /><br />It is also possible to visit the Royal Selangor Pewter Factory and Visitor Centre where one can delve into the process of pewter manufacturing and learn about its properties, while enjoying the fascinating pewter museum located on the premises of the factory.<br /><br />You will dropped off back to your hotel after finishing the tour.<br/><br/><b>Departure Time</b>: 9am or 12pm<br/><br/><b>Departure Point</b>: Your Hotel in Kuala Lumpur/Petaling Jaya<br/><br/><b>Operations</b>: Daily<br/><br/><b>Vourcher</b>: You can present either a paper or an electronic voucher for this activity.<br/><br/><b>Excerpt</b>: Join this full-day private tour exploring Kuala Lumpur lead by a professional English speaking driver/guide and get some local inside tips. This approximately 8 hours tour in Kuala Lumpur is a...<br/><br/><b>Inclusions:</b><br/>All taxes, fees and handling charges<br/>Professional English-speaking guide/driver<br/>Hotel pickup and drop-off<br/>Transport by private vehicle<br/><br/><b>Exclusions:</b><br/>Food and drinks<br/>Gratuities<br/>Any entrance fee<br/>Souvenir photos (available to purchase)<br/><br/><b>Additional Info:</b><br/>Confirmation will be received at time of booking<br/>The tour and itinerary may change or cancel without prior notice due to unforeseen circumstances (if any). You will be advised of the change as soon as possible or receive a full refund', null, null, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1', null, '1', '', '', null, '', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '', '', '2017-02-21 12:09:51', '6', '2017-02-21 12:18:07', '6', 'default');
INSERT INTO `product` VALUES ('212', '', 'https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/tly-production/partner_offers/images/000/007/105/medium/half-day-school-of-hard-knocks-and-royal-selangor-pewter-tour-in-kuala-lumpur-291993.jpg?1487621776', '', '7105', 'Half-Day School of Hard Knocks and Royal Selangor Pewter Tour', 'Experience fun and excitement with the chance to make your own pewter creation. Showcase your artistic talents and de-stress with a hammer while expressing your creativity in pewtersmithing workshop at Royal Selangor Pewter. <br /><br />In two separate sessions, you will be guided through the process of creating a pewter dish using traditional tools such as the hammer and wooden mold. You will learn the process of casting, polishing and decorating a pewter by an experienced instructor. At the end of the session, you will take home your own finished pewter dish.', 'From your hotel in Kuala Lumpur and  to the Royal Selangor Pewter, arrive at the Royal Selangor Visitor Center to be met by the house guide for a guided tour. Tour a house with more than a century of history.<br /><br />Founded in 1885, Royal Selangor is a well-known name in quality pewter, a brand synonymous with design and craftsmanship. In the hands of skilled craftspeople, this versatile alloy of tin, copper and antimony is transformed into an endless variety of home ware and gifts sold in more than twenty countries around the world. The Visitor Centre takes you back over a hundred years to the founding of Royal Selangor and its inextricable link with the history of Malaysia, to the present day as the world’s largest pewter maker and its expansion into gold and sterling silver.<br /><br />After the house tour, head into the workshop area and get ready for a fun expression of your creativity. Learn a bit more about the importance of the pewter, fine jewelry, and silver industry to Malaysia before sitting down at your work station. Your guide will provide you with all the tools necessary to create your finished product, including a hammer and wooden mold. Learn the secrets of master craftsmen as you run through a 30-minute session to make your own pewter dish.<br /><br />Thereafter, head to the second workshop station, to learn the process of casting, polishing, and decorating a pewter accessory. Here, bring out your artistic side to create an intricate, sparkling pewter dish and at the end of your 60-minute lesson, you will feel like an expert in the pewter-making process and leave with a new pewter accessory of your own. <br /><br />Finish your workshop with a cool souvenir to show off to your friends and family, as well as a personalized certificate of completion (certificate only for School of Hard Knocks).<br /><br />At the end of the tour you will be taken back to your hotel.<br/><br/><b>Departure Time</b>: Morning Departure: 9am<br />Afternoon Departure: 2pm<br/><br/><b>Departure Point</b>: Centrally located Kuala Lumpur hotels (selected hotels only)<br/><br/><b>Operations</b>: Daily<br/><br/><b>Vourcher</b>: You can present either a paper or an electronic voucher for this activity.<br/><br/><b>Excerpt</b>: Experience fun and excitement with the chance to make your own pewter creation. Showcase your artistic talents and de-stress with a hammer while expressing your creativity in pewtersmithing...<br/><br/><b>Inclusions:</b><br/>Separate Guided Workshop of School of Hard Knocks (30 minutes) and The Foundry at Royal Selangor Pewter (60 minutes)<br/>Guided house tour of the Royal Selangor Visitor Centre<br/>Admission fees<br/>Own created pewter dish<br/>Certificate of completion (School of Hard Knocks only)<br/>English speaking services<br/>Hotel pickup and drop-off (selected hotels within city centre)<br/><br/><b>Exclusions:</b><br/>Food and drinks<br/>Pickup and Drop-off Surcharge for hotels not located within the zone (Ampang, Gombak, KL Sentral, Brickfields, Putrajaya, Cyberjaya, Seri Kembangan, Serdang, Petaling Jaya, Subang, Klang, Bangi, Sunway)<br/><br/><b>Additional Info:</b><br/>Confirmation will be received within 48 hours of booking, subject to availability<br/>A minimum of 2 people per booking is required<br/>Adult pricing applies to all travelers<br/>Children must be accompanied by parents<br/>A moderate amount of walking is involved', null, null, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1', null, '1', '', '', null, '', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '', '', '2017-02-21 12:09:51', '6', '2017-02-21 12:18:07', '6', 'default');
INSERT INTO `product` VALUES ('213', '', 'https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/tly-production/partner_offers/images/000/007/106/medium/private-tour-delicious-bak-kut-teh-food-tour-in-klang-in-kuala-lumpur-309448.jpg?1459455352', '', '7106', 'Private Tour: Delicious Bak Kut Teh Food Tour in Klang', 'Join this private half-day tour to experience a famous and delicious Bak Kut Teh (meat bone herbal tea soup) in Klang, Selangor. This is one of the most popular local Chinese Hokkien delicacy and a must try dishes during your holiday in Malaysia. The tour including a round-trip hotel transfer in KL area.', 'Join this approximately 4-5 hour amazing food tour at the famous restaurant in Klang, Selangor and taste the delicious Bak Kut Teh (meat bone herbal tea soup). There are a few departure options for the tour: We will departing at 7:30pm on Thursday and Friday tour, and we have another 2 options on Saturday which start at 11am morning and 6pm for dinner.<br /><br />You will be picked up from your hotel in Kuala Lumpur and heading to Klang. We will arrive at the famous Bak Kut Teh restaurant after an hour ride and you are ready to try the delicious Bak Kut Teh dishes (meat bone herbal tea soup), in both soup and dry type. <br /><br />The ingredient used to cook the Bak Kut Teh consist of pork ribs and herbs such as tong kui, some spices include cinnamon, cloves, garlic and star anise. The pork ribs are boiled in the herbs for hours until the meat become tender. The common way of taking Bak Kut Teh is always with Chinese tea and rice. <br /><br />We spend 1.5-2 hours at the restaurant and rest assured that you will be sinking in your teeth into this delicious local Chinese Hokkien food. You will be transported back to your hotel safely after dinner.<br/><br/><b>Departure Time</b>: Thursday and Friday: 7.30pm<br />Saturday: 11am or 6pm<br/><br/><b>Departure Point</b>: Your hotel in KL only<br/><br/><b>Operations</b>: Thursday, Friday and Saturday<br/><br/><b>Vourcher</b>: You can present either a paper or an electronic voucher for this activity.<br/><br/><b>Excerpt</b>: Join this private half-day tour to experience a famous and delicious Bak Kut Teh (meat bone herbal tea soup) in Klang, Selangor. This is one of the most popular local Chinese Hokkien delicacy and a...<br/><br/><b>Inclusions:</b><br/>Private small-group tour<br/>Professional English speaking local guide and driver<br/>Fuel surcharge and local taxes<br/>Dinner, beverage and snacks<br/>Hotel pickup and drop-off (KL area only)<br/><br/><b>Exclusions:</b><br/>Excess luggage charges (where applicable)<br/><br/><b>Additional Info:</b><br/>Confirmation will be received at time of booking<br/>Children must be accompanied by an adult', null, null, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', null, null, '1', '', '', null, '', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '', '', '2017-02-21 12:09:52', '6', '2017-02-21 12:18:08', '6', 'default');
INSERT INTO `product` VALUES ('214', '', 'https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/tly-production/partner_offers/images/000/007/107/medium/full-day-private-tour-kuala-lumpur-city-and-countryside-in-kuala-lumpur-302389.jpg?1487621738', '', '7107', 'Private Full-Day Tour of Kuala Lumpur City and the Batu Caves', 'Join this private full-day Kuala Lumpur city and countryside tour to explore historical buildings and some of the most popular attractions such as National Mosque, King Palace, Independence Square, Old Railway Station, Batu Caves, Lake Garden, National Monument, Parliament House and Royal Selangor.<br /><br />The trip will include a photography opportunity at the Petronas Twin Towers, the tallest twin towers in the world. Please note: the tickets for this attraction are not included in this tour.', 'Join this full-day private tour to experience the local lifestyle, culture and learn some history of Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia.<br /><br />Despite the growing skyline of a modern metropolis, Kuala Lumpur has always been charming and full of character. You will see the Petronas Twin Towers, the world tallest twin towers, The King\'s Palace (Istana Negara) a symbol of Malaysian sovereignty, the Independence Square (Merdeka Square) and the National Museum (Merdeka Square).<br /><br />You will drive past the Lake Gardens (Perdana Botanical Gardens), where you can find over 5,000 birds flying freely and accustomed to being around people. View the National Monument, National Mosque (Masjid Negara), and the Old Railway Station (Railway Station and Administration Building). <br /><br />Next, you\'ll move on to the Royal Selangor Visitor Center to appreciate the Malaysian pewter arts, followed by a short drive through Little India. Malaysia\'s official Little India in Brickfields used to be a simple residential neighborhood just outside Kuala Lumpur, but now has transformed into a colorful community with stores and restaurants along the streets. <br /><br />After the trip through Little India, you\'ll arrive at the Batu Caves. This natural phenomenon is a massive limestone outcrop, with its interiors home to a Hindu shrine lined with different deities. The shrine itself is located deep inside the high caverns which take 272 steps to reach. Last stop is a local Malaysian Batik center to see how the fabric is being designed and printed.<br/><br/><b>Departure Time</b>: 9am<br/><br/><b>Departure Point</b>: Your hotel in Kuala Lumpur city area<br/><br/><b>Operations</b>: Daily<br/><br/><b>Vourcher</b>: You can present either a paper or an electronic voucher for this activity.<br/><br/><b>Excerpt</b>: Join this private full-day Kuala Lumpur city and countryside tour to explore historical buildings and some of the most popular attractions such as National Mosque, King Palace, Independence Square...<br/><br/><b>Inclusions:</b><br/>Air-conditioned private van<br/>Professional and experienced guide<br/>All taxes and service charges<br/>Hotel pickup and drop-off (selected hotels only)<br/><br/><b>Exclusions:</b><br/>Personal expenses<br/>Food and drinks<br/>Petronas Twin Towers Sky bridge tickets<br/><br/><b>Additional Info:</b><br/>Confirmation will be received at time of booking<br/>Child rate applies only when sharing with 2 paying adults<br/>Group discount is available for group size of 2, 4 or more<br/>A maximum of 15 people per booking', null, null, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1', null, '1', '', '', null, '', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '', '', '2017-02-21 12:09:53', '6', '2017-02-21 12:18:09', '6', 'default');
INSERT INTO `product` VALUES ('215', '', 'https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/tly-production/partner_offers/images/000/007/108/medium/day-trip-sunway-lagoon-theme-park-with-round-trip-transfer-and-lunch-in-kuala-lumpur-245513.jpg?1459455358', '', '7108', 'Day Trip Sunway Lagoon Theme Park with Round-Trip Transfer and Lunch', 'Come and enjoy Sunway Lagoon Theme Park, a place for non-stop fun and entertainment. Have a relaxing and comfortable return transfer from Kuala Lumpur City Center hotels to Sunway Lagoon Theme Park. Sunway Lagoon Theme Park is absolutely a best attraction for family and friends. Relish your holiday tour with smiles and laughter.', 'You\'ll get a two way transfer to Sunway Lagoon Theme Park from Kuala Lumpur City Center hotels on private basic (PVT). These transfers are between Kuala Lumpur City Center hotels to Sunway Lagoon Theme Park by van (Toyota Hiace or Hyundai Starex). The pickup and drop off services session will be between 9am - 6pm daily and the journey duration will be approximately 45 minutes. <br /><br />Upon arrival, your guide will assist you to collect your entrance ticket at the ticketing counter and complimentary food voucher. The ticket will allow you to access all 5 parks: Water Park, Amusement Park, Wildlife Park, Extreme Park, and Scream Park. <br /><br />In Sunway Lagoon Explore the world’s largest man-made surf beach with an area over 13,000 sf. It will boost your excitement while catching the perfect wave each time. It is also home to the world’s largest water ride, Vuvuzela, and to the first Waterplexx 5D, Malaysia’s first FlowRider, and many other great attractions.<br /><br />Hop on board Pirate’s Revenge, Malaysia’s first 360-degree Rotating Pirate Ship. Scream your way along the ride on the Lost City of Gold Scream Coaster.<br /><br />Captain kids Playland and Captain Kid’s Candy land are themed playgrounds that are designed especially for kids. Kids will have tons of fun at these 2 newly designed attractions.<br /><br />Challenge yourself at adrenaline-pumping fun at Extreme Park. Hit the bulls eye at the Archery Target Shooting Range, go off-road on an all-terrain vehicle (ATV), or satisfy your need for speed on a go-kart.<br /><br />Helicopters are waiting to rescue you but to reach them you have to make your way through an industrial complex swarming with zombies. World War Z! Live is just one of the highlights of the Scream Park that features no less than 3 floors of fear.<br /><br />Ground zero is turned into World War Z! Live. This is the latest addition to Lynton V. Harris’s Scream Park, based on the blockbuster movie starring Brad Pitt. The walk-through scare attraction places you firmly in the middle of the war against zombies.<br /><br />Once you have completed your excursion, return back to your hotel in a comfortable air-conditioned private vehicle.<br/><br/><b>Departure Time</b>: 9:30am<br/><br/><b>Departure Point</b>: Your hotel in Kuala Lumpur city area<br/><br/><b>Operations</b>: Daily<br/><br/><b>Vourcher</b>: You can present either a paper or an electronic voucher for this activity.<br/><br/><b>Excerpt</b>: Come and enjoy Sunway Lagoon Theme Park, a place for non-stop fun and entertainment. Have a relaxing and comfortable return transfer from Kuala Lumpur City Center hotels to Sunway Lagoon Theme...<br/><br/><b>Inclusions:</b><br/>Lunch (Coupon)<br/>Admission and entrance tickets to 5 parks (Water Park, Amusement Park, Wildlife Park, Extreme Park and Scream Park)<br/>English-speaking guide/driver<br/>Hotel pickup and drop-off by private vehicle<br/><br/><b>Exclusions:</b><br/>Souvenir photos (available to purchase)<br/>Gratuities (optional)<br/>There is additional fees for the following rides in Go Cart, Bungy Jump and G-Force X<br/><br/><b>Additional Info:</b><br/>Confirmation will be received at time of booking<br/>Children must be accompanied by an adult<br/>Please carry along your own towel and swimwear<br/>Please note pickups and drop-offs are within the Kuala Lumpur city center only', null, null, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1', null, '1', '', '', null, '', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '', '', '2017-02-21 12:09:53', '6', '2017-02-21 12:18:10', '6', 'default');
INSERT INTO `product` VALUES ('216', '', 'https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/tly-production/partner_offers/images/000/008/137/medium/lotus-leaves-painting-in-kuala-lumpur-in-kuala-lumpur-310853.jpg?1461874573', '', '8137', 'Lotus Leaves Painting in Kuala Lumpur', 'Book this small group lotus leaves painting lesson and unleash your inner artisan with maximum 5 students per lesson for approximately 3 hours. Be immersed in the enriching experience of creating your Asian masterpiece.  Lotus leaves painting does not require any skills or experience in art whatsoever. Simply pick the colors you love and harmonize them on your canvas. These gorgeous paintings make lovely, meaningful gifts for home and office decor and are guaranteed to be delightful conversation pieces. Whether you choose ethereal warm or vibrant colors, your painting will captivate its audience and inspire any space it fills.', 'Simple painting techniques will be demonstrated to get you started and your friendly facilitators will be right there with you; providing guidance at any moment you need throughout the workshop. Don’t fret over making mistakes because the beauty of lotus leaves painting is that you can simply do them over. So let loose your inhibitions and set the infinite palette of your imagination free.<br /><br />Experiment with colors fearlessly and watch as every brush stroke unfolds a beautiful new layer into something stunning that is uniquely yours.  Rest assured that you’re in good hands with our facilitators who will provide you with everything you need in terms of guidance and tools. You will be completely at ease during this fun and highly interactive workshop. <br /><br />Lotus leaves painting is about the harmonization of colors and tones, so here are some helpful tips given during the lessons. Please feel free to bring photos, books, items or materials that you feel may help your color creativity during the workshop. We will be on hand to prompt you in the right direction! <br /><br />You will have a choice of various sizes of canvases and all you need to do is choose which size you would love to paint on at the beginning of the workshop.<br/><br/><b>Departure Time</b>: 9:30am<br/><br/><b>Departure Point</b>: Home Studio - Himapan Malaysia <br />(Tiara Ampang Condominium Jalan Ampang,68000 Selangor)<br/><br/><b>Operations</b>: Daily<br/><br/><b>Vourcher</b>: You can present either a paper or an electronic voucher for this activity.<br/><br/><b>Excerpt</b>: Book this small group lotus leaves painting lesson and unleash your inner artisan with maximum 5 students per lesson for approximately 3 hours. Be immersed in the enriching experience of creating...<br/><br/><b>Inclusions:</b><br/>Painting apparatus, acrylic paints, apron,light refreshments, packaging for the canvas and DIY varnishing kit <br/><br/><b>Exclusions:</b><br/>Varnishing services, available upon request<br/>Worldwide delivery available upon request<br/><br/><b>Additional Info:</b><br/>Confirmation will be received at time of booking, unless booked within 7 days of travel. In this case confirmation will be received within 48 hours, subject to availability<br/>Appointment required and subject to availability', null, null, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1', null, '1', '', '', null, '', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '', '', '2017-02-21 12:09:54', '6', '2017-02-21 12:18:10', '6', 'default');
INSERT INTO `product` VALUES ('217', '', 'https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/tly-production/offers/images/000/000/205/medium/Malaysia_Heritage_Walk.jpg?1404116390', '', '205', 'Malaysia Heritage Walk', 'Travel through Malaysia’s past to the present. Experience the richness and grandeur of Malaysia’s cultural heritage. Indulge in Malaysia’s exquisite and breathtaking wonders of nature.', 'We are a bunch of locals who are deeply concerned with the continuous decline in the levels of awareness of the Malaysian cultural heritage due to the rapid development of the country. We recognize the tough challenge of sustainably conserving Malaysia’s living proofs of a rich and colorful culture.\r\n\r\nBut we are a determined group of Malaysians who stand undaunted by the challenges modern civilization has posed – we are hopeful and positive that we will be able to contribute in the development of a stronger and more heartfelt pride for the history of Malaysia and celebrate the living legacies of Malaysia’s grand past.\r\n\r\nWe serve as a hub for Malaysia’s heritage walks and guided tours. We promote these nature and culture – themed tours to protect Malaysia’s history, culture and old architecture as well as save and preserve the environment. What’s more, in a way, we also help the locals have better livelihoods.\r\n\r\n** Additional Details** \r\n\r\nAddress:\r\n02-03 Mezzanine Floor, \r\nCentral Market Annexe, \r\nJalan Hang Kasturi, 50050 Kuala Lumpur, \r\nFederal Territory of Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia\r\n\r\nTel No: \r\n(60) 3-20321031/20321032\r\n\r\nMobile No: \r\n(60) 17-9891031\r\n\r\nEmail:\r\nbetourist@ymail.com\r\n\r\n(Source: http://www.malaysiaheritage.net/) <br/><br/><b>Departure Time</b>: <br/><br/><b>Departure Point</b>: <br/><br/><b>Operations</b>: <br/><br/><b>Vourcher</b>: <br/><br/><b>Excerpt</b>: Travel through Malaysia’s past to the present. Experience the richness and grandeur of Malaysia’s cultural heritage. Indulge in Malaysia’s exquisite and breathtaking wonders of nature.<br/><br/><b>Inclusions:</b><br/><br/><br/><b>Exclusions:</b><br/><br/><br/><b>Additional Info:</b><br/>', null, null, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', null, null, '1', '', '', null, '', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '', '', '2017-02-21 12:09:55', '6', '2017-02-21 12:18:11', '6', 'default');
INSERT INTO `product` VALUES ('218', '', 'https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/tly-production/partner_offers/images/000/008/142/medium/private-one-way-kuala-lumpur-airport-arrival-transfer-in-kuala-lumpur-324665.jpg?1461961040', '', '8142', 'Private One-Way Kuala Lumpur Airport Arrival Transfer', 'Pre-book your private one-way arrival transfer from Kuala Lumpur International Airport (KLIA1 or KLIA2) and transport you to your selected hotel in Kuala Lumpur or Petaling Jaya areas. You will be greeted by our guide at the arrival hall and enjoy a comfortable ride in our air-conditioned vehicle.Please note this is a private transfer group price.', 'This private budget transfer service will take you to your next destination in comfort. We serve both Kuala Lumpur International Airport KLIA1 and KLIA2 and a private transfer either to the Kuala Lumpur city or Petaling Jaya area. <br /><br />Our English speaking driver will meet and greet you at your arrival terminal exit gate. He will make your booking easy and transfer relaxed. With space for up to 7 passengers we can also cater for larger groups or families. Take the stress out of airport transfers and book in early with our dedicated and responsible drivers to get you there on time.<br/><br/><b>Departure Time</b>: Flexible between 7am-10pm<br/><br/><b>Departure Point</b>: Your hotel in Kuala Lumpur/Petaling Jaya area<br/><br/><b>Operations</b>: Daily<br/><br/><b>Vourcher</b>: You can present either a paper or an electronic voucher for this activity.<br/><br/><b>Excerpt</b>: Pre-book your private one-way arrival transfer from Kuala Lumpur International Airport (KLIA1 or KLIA2) and transport you to your selected hotel in Kuala Lumpur or Petaling Jaya areas. You will be...<br/><br/><b>Inclusions:</b><br/>One-way private transfer<br/>Local taxes<br/>Hotel drop-off<br/><br/><b>Exclusions:</b><br/>Personal expense<br/>Transportation to/from attractions<br/><br/><b>Additional Info:</b><br/>Confirmation will be received at time of booking<br/>Duration of transfer is depend on traffic conditions<br/>Each traveler is allowed a maximum of 1 suitcase and 1 carry-on bag. Oversized or excessive luggage (e.g. surfboards, golf clubs or bikes) may have certain restrictions, please inquire with the operator prior to travel to confirm if your excess luggage is acceptable', null, null, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1', null, '1', '', '', null, '', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '', '', '2017-02-21 12:09:55', '6', '2017-02-21 12:18:12', '6', 'default');
INSERT INTO `product` VALUES ('219', '', 'https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/tly-production/offers/images/000/000/207/medium/Islamic_Art_Museum.jpg?1404116640', '', '207', 'Islamic Art Museum', 'The Islamic Arts Museum houses more than seven thousand artifacts, as well as an exceptional library of Islamic art books.', 'Interest in Islamic art has grown enormously in recent years. Reflecting this awareness, in December 1998, Malaysia became home to Southeast Asia’s largest museum of Islamic art. The building occupies 30,000 square meters and is situated amid the leafy surroundings of central Kuala Lumpur’s Lake Gardens.\r\n\r\nThe museum is home to more than seven thousand artifacts, as well has an exceptional library of Islamic-art books. The art objects on display range from the tiniest pieces of jewelry to one of the world’s largest scale models of the Masjid al-Haram in Mecca. The aim is to create a collection that is truly representative of the Islamic world.\r\n\r\nInstead of concentrating on works from the heartlands of Persia and the Middle East, the muzeum also puts the emphasis on Asia with China and Southeast Asia especially well-represented. The third component of the Malaysian melting pot is India, which is also given special status. Other parts of the collection are displayed according to type rather than geographical origins in the museum’s twelve galleries.\r\n\r\n**Additional Details:** \r\nAddress: Jalan Lembah Perdana, 50480 Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia. \r\nTel No: +60 3-2274 2020\r\nEmail: info@iamm.org.my\r\n\r\n*(Source: http://www.iamm.org.my/)*<br/><br/><b>Departure Time</b>: <br/><br/><b>Departure Point</b>: <br/><br/><b>Operations</b>: <br/><br/><b>Vourcher</b>: <br/><br/><b>Excerpt</b>: The Islamic Arts Museum houses more than seven thousand artifacts, as well as an exceptional library of Islamic art books.<br/><br/><b>Inclusions:</b><br/><br/><br/><b>Exclusions:</b><br/><br/><br/><b>Additional Info:</b><br/>', null, null, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', null, null, '1', '', '', null, '', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '', '', '2017-02-21 12:09:56', '6', '2017-02-21 12:18:12', '6', 'default');
INSERT INTO `product` VALUES ('220', '', 'https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/tly-production/partner_offers/images/000/008/143/medium/sunway-lagoon-trip-with-round-trip-private-transfer-in-kuala-lumpur-325187.jpg?1487621775', '', '8143', 'Sunway Lagoon Admission with Round-Trip Private Transfer', 'Sunway Lagoon Malaysia theme park offers visitors six separate attractions at this multi-themed destination. Travel round-trip at your preferred time with an included private transfer from your hotel in Kuala Lumpur and Petaling Jaya. Vehicles can accommodate groups of up to seven people, with a photo stop at the Petronas Twin Towers.', 'Magically transformed from the site of an old tin mine and quarry, Sunway Lagoon is one of Malaysia’s largest theme parks. Set amid beautifully landscaped surroundings, Sunway Lagoon lets you plummet and plunge from plentiful rides and slides among 80 family-friendly attractions of international standard. The park contains themed lands and adventure zones — including the Water Park, Amusement Park, Wildlife Park, Extreme Park, Nickelodeon Lost Lagoon, and Scream Park — offering an ideal escape for children and playful adults alike.<br /><br />Round-trip transportation by private, 7-passenger vehicle from your Kuala Lumpur or Petaling Jaya hotel is included on this day trip with a driver and guide. The tour includes stops at leather and batik factories as well as photo ops at the Petronas Twin Towers along the way.<br/><br/><b>Departure Time</b>: Opening hours: 10am - 6pm<br/><br/><b>Departure Point</b>: Your hotel in Kuala Lumpur or Petaling Jaya<br/><br/><b>Operations</b>: Daily<br/><br/><b>Vourcher</b>: You can present either a paper or an electronic voucher for this activity.<br/><br/><b>Excerpt</b>: Sunway Lagoon Malaysia theme park offers visitors six separate attractions at this multi-themed destination. Travel round-trip at your preferred time with an included private transfer from your...<br/><br/><b>Inclusions:</b><br/>Professional driver and guide<br/>Transport by private, air-conditioned vehicle<br/>Entrance fees to the following parks: World of Adventure, Wild Wild West, Waters of Africa, Extreme Park, Nickelodeon Lost Lagoon and Scream Park<br/>Hotel pickup and drop-off<br/><br/><b>Exclusions:</b><br/>The following rides in the Extreme Park: Bungy Jump, G-Force X and Go Cart<br/>Food and drinks<br/><br/><b>Additional Info:</b><br/>Confirmation will be received at time of booking<br/>A moderate amount of walking is involved<br/>Please bring your own swimwear<br/>A minimum of 2 people per booking is required', null, null, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1', null, '1', '', '', null, '', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '', '', '2017-02-21 12:09:57', '6', '2017-02-21 12:18:13', '6', 'default');
INSERT INTO `product` VALUES ('221', '', 'https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/tly-production/partner_offers/images/000/008/146/medium/kuala-lumpur-day-tour-from-port-klang-cruise-terminal-in-kuala-lumpur-295784.jpg?1487621747', '', '8146', 'Kuala Lumpur Shore Excursion from Port Klang Cruise Terminal', 'Join this full-day tour depart from Port Klang Cruise Terminal (the north or south port) to explore Kuala Lumpur city before you return to your ship.<br /><br />This tour has been carefully concocted for cruise guests and will covers virtually a visit to KL Tower, Batu Caves, Little India, photo shoots at Twin Towers, Malaysia Independent Square and Royal Selangor Clubhouse. A delicious lunch on banana leaves will be served.', 'At 8-9:30am, you will be meet and greet at the cruise terminal which located 25miles (40km) from the city of Kuala Lumpur. You will catch a bird&rsquo;s eye view of the city from KL Tower before we proceed to Batu Caves. <br /><br />At Batu Caves, you will climb 272 steps into the Temple of Hindu Deity Lord Subramaniam who is honored during a festival called Thaipusam every year in January/February.&nbsp; His 140 feet gold painted statue is mesmerizing. Ladies need to be appropriately dressed to enter the temple. <br /><br />Next would be a visit to the Independent Square where Malaysia got her independence, St Mary\'s Cathedral and the Royal Selangor Clubhouse where cricket was once popular.<br /><br />After a short walk in Little India, lunch would be served on banana leaf.&nbsp; Eating on banana leaves is a custom that dates back thousands of years, however its benefits are still relevant today. After lunch, we will visit the Twin Towers for a free and easy, shopping and photo shoots before departing for the cruise terminal at 3pm.<br /><br /><strong>Worry-free Shore Excursion:</strong> <br />We will ensure your timely return to Port Klang for this activity. In the rare event your ship has departed, we will arrange for transportation to the next port-of-call. If your ship is delayed and you are unable to attend this activity, your money will be refunded. See our terms and conditions for full details.<br/><br/><b>Departure Time</b>: 8am<br/><br/><b>Departure Point</b>: Port Klang Cruise Terminal, Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia<br/><br/><b>Operations</b>: Daily<br/><br/><b>Vourcher</b>: You can present either a paper or an electronic voucher for this activity.<br/><br/><b>Excerpt</b>: Join this full-day tour depart from Port Klang Cruise Terminal (the north or south port) to explore Kuala Lumpur city before you return to your ship.This tour has been carefully...<br/><br/><b>Inclusions:</b><br/>Entrance fees<br/>Bottled water<br/>Lunch<br/><br/><b>Exclusions:</b><br/>Gratuities (optional)<br/>Alcoholic drinks (available to purchase)<br/><br/><b>Additional Info:</b><br/>Confirmation will be received at time of booking<br/>Child rate applies only when sharing with 2 paying adults<br/>Children must be accompanied by an adult<br/>Infant seats are available on request if advised at time of booking<br/>Refunds will not be issued if tour/activity is missed due to late or non-arrival of cruise ship<br/>Dress code is smart casual<br/>A small amount of walking is involved', null, null, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1', null, '1', '', '', null, '', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '', '', '2017-02-21 12:09:57', '6', '2017-02-21 12:18:14', '6', 'default');
INSERT INTO `product` VALUES ('222', '', 'https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/tly-production/offers/images/000/000/211/medium/Petronas_Twin_Tower.jpg?1404116751', '', '211', 'Petronas Twin Towers', 'Soaring to a height of 451.9 metres, the 88-storey twin structure is Kuala Lumpur\'s crown jewel.', 'Majestic by day and dazzling at night, the PETRONAS Twin Towers was inspired by Tun Mahathir Mohamad\'s vision for Malaysia to be a global player. Together with master architect Cesar Pelli, the international icon powerfully captures the nation\'s ambitions and aspirations. \r\n\r\nVisit and experience the PETRONAS Twin Towers first-hand. Begin your tour with interactive displays that showcase the journey, from idea to completion. Scale 170 metres in an elevator with a futuristic edge. The doors will open at the Skybridge, a connecting structure between the towers and the world\'s highest 2-storey bridge. Ascend even higher to level 86, where the story of Malaysia\'s vision unfolds amid breathtaking views of Kuala Lumpur. Then wrap up your visit with exquisite souvenirs at the gift shop. \r\n\r\n**Additional Details:** \r\n\r\nAddress: Kuala Lumpur City Centre, 50088 Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia\r\nTel. No: +603 2331 8080\r\n\r\n*(Source: http://www.tourism.gov.my/en/ir/web-page/places/states-of-malaysia/kuala-lumpur/petronas-twin-towers)*<br/><br/><b>Departure Time</b>: <br/><br/><b>Departure Point</b>: <br/><br/><b>Operations</b>: <br/><br/><b>Vourcher</b>: <br/><br/><b>Excerpt</b>: Soaring to a height of 451.9 metres, the 88-storey twin structure is Kuala Lumpur\'s crown jewel.<br/><br/><b>Inclusions:</b><br/><br/><br/><b>Exclusions:</b><br/><br/><br/><b>Additional Info:</b><br/>', null, null, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', null, null, '1', '', '', null, '', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '', '', '2017-02-21 12:09:58', '6', '2017-02-21 12:18:15', '6', 'default');
INSERT INTO `product` VALUES ('223', '', 'https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/tly-production/partner_offers/images/000/008/147/medium/kampong-village-tour-in-kuala-lumpur-in-kuala-lumpur-272117.jpg?1487621778', '', '8147', 'Kuala Lumpur Shore Excursion Mah Meri Sea Gypsies Cultural Village with Coconut Wine and Lunch', 'Join this full-day tour immersed in history and tradition that will give you real insight of the Old Malaysia. This tour starts from the Cruise Terminal in Port Klang and takes to the tribal area of the Mah Meri Village.<br />The Mah Meri is an indigenous Senoi tribe of aborigines, 2,000 remaining, livelihood depended on fishing and agriculture. They have been listed under UNESCO as a heritage site. Though soft spoken they excel in wood carving depicting mythological meanings with spiritual connections. We will also visit the Rumah Moyang Ancestral Home and much commentary by the resident villager.&nbsp;<br /><br />A typical Malay lunch will be served in a Malay home. All entrance fees, free flow of mineral water and chauffeur-guide services with return transfers back to the Cruise Terminal in Port Klang are included.', 'At 8am, you will be meet and greet at the Cruise Terminal in Port Klang where all cruise ships usually dock. An allowance of 2 hours is given for meet and greet due to dock congestion. Depart to a quaint village and meet the indigenous Senoi tribe of aborigines the Mah Meri who were sea gypsies depending on fish agriculture and now excel in wood carvings depicting rich mythological meanings with spiritual connections. Still remaining &nbsp;2,000 of them to keep their culture going.The village guide will show us around not forgetting the Rumah Moyang Ancestral Home where food and drinks are offered to the ancestors in return for protection from evil. A simple wood carving and origami awaits. <br /><br />At 11:30am visit a coconut plantation&nbsp;to watch the tapping of coconut wine (toddy), a practice copied from India. It has an alcohol content of 4% and a health drink. <br /><br />We then proceed to a typical Malay home for an herbal garden tour led by the owner and a delicious home cooked lunch will be served. After lunch, we will drive past scenic houses on stilts with photo shoots along the way. We will stop by at a coconut wine shop for some exotic snacks with a cup of toddy.<br /><br />Around 4pm, we will depart to cruise terminal.<br/><br/><b>Departure Time</b>: 8am<br/><br/><b>Departure Point</b>: Cruise Terminal Port Klang<br/><br/><b>Operations</b>: Daily<br/><br/><b>Vourcher</b>: You can present either a paper or an electronic voucher for this activity.<br/><br/><b>Excerpt</b>: Join this full-day tour immersed in history and tradition that will give you real insight of the Old Malaysia. This tour starts from the Cruise Terminal in Port Klang and takes to the tribal area...<br/><br/><b>Inclusions:</b><br/>Bottled water and lunch<br/>Local wine tasting<br/><br/><b>Exclusions:</b><br/>Alcoholic drinks (available to purchase)<br/><br/><b>Additional Info:</b><br/>Confirmation will be received at time of booking<br/>Child rate applies only when sharing with 2 paying adults<br/>Infant meals not included', null, null, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1', null, '1', '', '', null, '', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '', '', '2017-02-21 12:09:59', '6', '2017-02-21 12:18:15', '6', 'default');
INSERT INTO `product` VALUES ('224', '', 'https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/tly-production/offers/images/000/000/214/medium/Royal_Selangor_Pewter_Factory.JPG?1404116973', '', '214', 'Royal Selangor Pewter Factory & Visitor Centre', 'Every story has a beginning and Royal Selangor’s coincides with the remarkable development of tin mining in the Malay Peninsula in the 1800s. Traditional pewtersmithing tools and antique pewter from around the world are showcased in the Pewter Museum, and ancient tin currency is featured.', 'Founded in 1885, Royal Selangor is the world’s foremost name in quality pewter, a brand synonymous with design and craftsmanship. In the hands of our skilled craftspeople, this versatile alloy of tin, copper and antimony is transformed into an endless variety of homeware and gifts sold in more than twenty countries around the world.\r\n\r\nThe Visitor Centre takes you back over a hundred years to the founding of Royal Selangor and its inextricable link with the history of Malaysia, to the present day as the world’s largest pewter maker and its expansion into gold and sterling silver.\r\n\r\n**Additional Details:** \r\n\r\nAddress: No. 4, Jalan Usahawan 6, Setapak Jaya, 53300 Kuala Lumpur.\r\nTel No: +603 4145 6122\r\nEmail: visitorcentre@royalselangor.com.my\r\n\r\n*(Source: http://visitorcentre.royalselangor.com/)*<br/><br/><b>Departure Time</b>: <br/><br/><b>Departure Point</b>: <br/><br/><b>Operations</b>: <br/><br/><b>Vourcher</b>: <br/><br/><b>Excerpt</b>: Every story has a beginning and Royal Selangor’s coincides with the remarkable development of tin mining in the Malay Peninsula in the 1800s. Traditional pewtersmithing tools and antique pewter...<br/><br/><b>Inclusions:</b><br/><br/><br/><b>Exclusions:</b><br/><br/><br/><b>Additional Info:</b><br/>', null, null, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', null, null, '1', '', '', null, '', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '', '', '2017-02-21 12:09:59', '6', '2017-02-21 12:18:16', '6', 'default');
INSERT INTO `product` VALUES ('225', '', 'https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/tly-production/offers/images/000/000/218/medium/Kuala_Lumpur_Bird_Park.jpg?1404117270', '', '218', 'Kuala Lumpur Bird Park', 'Located in the serene and scenic Kuala Lumpur Lake Gardens, it is only 10 minutes drive away from the city centre of Kuala Lumpur. It is the home to more than 3,000 birds of approximately 200 species of local and foreign birds.', 'Sprawling approximately 20.9 acres of verdant valley terrain, the park is divided into 4 zones: Zone 1 and 2 make up the free-flight zone: Zone 3 is the Hornbill Park and Zone 4 is where the birds are placed in separate cages and mini aviaries.\r\n\r\nOne of KL Bird Park\'s most extraordinary feature is that in Zone 1, 2 and 3, birds are let free in the aviary which closely resembles their natural habitat. With this free-flight concept, birds are able to breed naturally in this unique environment.\r\n\r\nVisitors will have an exciting experience of watching colourful and melodic birds perching and winging about freely while relaxing in a natural and beautifully landscaped surrounding. KL Bird Park is also reputed to be the largest walk-in free-flight aviary in the world.\r\n\r\n**Additional Details** \r\n\r\nAddress: \r\n920 Jalan Cenderawasih, \r\n50480 Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia\r\n\r\nTel No: \r\n03 - 2272 1010\r\n\r\nFax No: \r\n03 - 2273 5428\r\n\r\nEmail: \r\ninfo@klbirdpark.com\r\n\r\n(Source: http://www.klbirdpark.com/) <br/><br/><b>Departure Time</b>: <br/><br/><b>Departure Point</b>: <br/><br/><b>Operations</b>: <br/><br/><b>Vourcher</b>: <br/><br/><b>Excerpt</b>: Located in the serene and scenic Kuala Lumpur Lake Gardens, it is only 10 minutes drive away from the city centre of Kuala Lumpur. It is the home to more than 3,000 birds of approximately 200...<br/><br/><b>Inclusions:</b><br/><br/><br/><b>Exclusions:</b><br/><br/><br/><b>Additional Info:</b><br/>', null, null, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', null, null, '1', '', '', null, 